<i>Under this murky sky,</i>

239
00:15:45,883 --> 00:15:50,850
<i>He struggled and struggled,
and this is how he’s gonna die</i>

240
00:15:51,329 --> 00:15:56,887
<i>Now, I’ll go take this “inheritance”</i>

241
00:15:57,420 --> 00:16:03,489
<i>I’ll use any means, yes,
to set me on my path</i>

242
00:16:06,621 --> 00:16:11,977
<i>I may have nothing in my hands yet,</i>

243
00:16:12,818 --> 00:16:18,021
<i>That means I’ll start from here</i>

244
00:16:19,336 --> 00:16:24,433
<i>Tell me, Joestar, in the sky over you,</i>

245
00:16:25,112 --> 00:16:32,286
<i>Is the sun shining?</i>

246
00:16:33,789 --> 00:16:38,050
<i>It is, isn’t it, Joestar?</i>

247
00:16:57,191 --> 00:16:58,512
Oh yeah!

248
00:16:58,537 --> 00:17:01,509
You’ve got something good today too, eh?

249
00:17:01,534 --> 00:17:02,732
Give it back!

250
00:17:03,548 --> 00:17:04,548
Over here!

251
00:17:05,214 --> 00:17:11,198
Hey Erina, I heard that
your old man’s a quack!

252
00:17:11,243 --> 00:17:13,019
My father’s a real doctor!

253
00:17:13,055 --> 00:17:17,557
Oh really? This hat looks expensive!

254
00:17:17,600 --> 00:17:20,433
Stop it! It was a birthday
present from my mother!

255
00:17:20,460 --> 00:17:22,190
Stop right there!

256
00:17:24,342 --> 00:17:26,913
What are you doing?! Take this!

257
00:17:31,449 --> 00:17:35,888
I hate when guys try to
act cool in front of girls!

258
00:17:36,140 --> 00:17:38,313
Ow! That hurt!

259
00:17:36,956 --> 00:17:39,946
-Hey, do you know who this guy is?

260
00:17:40,017 --> 00:17:42,374
If he’s that Jonathan kid
from the Joestar family,

261
00:17:42,404 --> 00:17:45,252
I’m gonna give him even
more of a walloping!

262
00:17:46,473 --> 00:17:47,473
Ah-ha!

263
00:17:48,170 --> 00:17:52,837
He <i>is</i> the Joestars’ Jonathan!

264
00:17:56,325 --> 00:18:00,476
Snotty little rich boy! You think
you’re so high and mighty?

265
00:18:03,671 --> 00:18:04,671
Danny!

266
00:18:05,284 --> 00:18:06,284
Eh?!

267
00:18:06,928 --> 00:18:09,421
Let’s go already! Shit!

268
00:18:13,094 --> 00:18:14,642
Uh... Are you alright?

269
00:18:14,658 --> 00:18:15,729
Leave me alone!

270
00:18:15,778 --> 00:18:16,222
But...

271
00:18:16,260 --> 00:18:18,220
I did this because I wanted to.

272
00:18:18,245 --> 00:18:20,269
I didn’t do it to get you to thank me.

273
00:18:21,773 --> 00:18:24,542
My goal is to become a true gentleman.

274
00:18:25,055 --> 00:18:29,230
You were a damsel in distress,
so I had to stand up for you.

275
00:18:32,688 --> 00:18:34,518
I’ll beat them, someday.

276
00:18:37,038 --> 00:18:38,292
Let’s go, Danny!

277
00:18:38,330 --> 00:18:39,430
Oh, wait!

278
00:18:47,212 --> 00:18:48,833
Jonathan Joestar...

279
00:19:23,513 --> 00:19:24,513
You...

280
00:19:25,162 --> 00:19:26,718
You must be Dio Brando!

281
00:19:27,750 --> 00:19:29,926
And you’re...

282
00:19:30,306 --> 00:19:31,473
Jonathan Joestar?

283
00:19:31,494 --> 00:19:33,807
Everyone calls me JoJo. Nice to meet you!

284
00:19:34,322 --> 00:19:36,122
Ah, Danny! I’ll introduce you.

285
00:19:36,172 --> 00:19:38,657
This is my friend, Danny.
He’s a clever old hound!

286
00:19:38,845 --> 00:19:41,115
Oh, and don’t worry about him biting!

287
00:19:41,158 --> 00:19:42,158
Friend?

288
00:19:42,209 --> 00:19:43,198
Yeah!

289
00:19:46,144 --> 00:19:48,168
Danny! What was that for!

290
00:19:48,186 --> 00:19:49,186
Danny!

291
00:19:50,113 --> 00:19:51,273
You won’t get away with this!

292
00:19:51,296 --> 00:19:53,969
We’ve been waiting for you, Dio Brando.

293
00:19:56,067 --> 00:19:57,067
Lord Joestar!

294
00:19:57,587 --> 00:19:59,026
Come inside!

295
00:19:59,794 --> 00:20:03,971
From today on, you’ll be
living here in our mansion.

296
00:20:05,479 --> 00:20:06,825
Something wrong, JoJo?

297
00:20:07,077 --> 00:20:08,277
Ah, nothing.

298
00:20:09,014 --> 00:20:12,079
You’ve travelled all the way from
London, Dio. You must be tired.

299
00:20:12,355 --> 00:20:15,653
Starting today, you are part of our family.

300
00:20:16,010 --> 00:20:19,785
You’ll be given the same
kind of life as my son, JoJo.

301
00:20:19,843 --> 00:20:20,478
Yes!

302
00:20:20,499 --> 00:20:23,292
I am grateful for your
kindness, Lord Joestar.

303
00:20:24,706 --> 00:20:25,706
Mister Brando!

304
00:20:26,101 --> 00:20:27,750
I’m Police Inspector Archer!

305
00:20:28,526 --> 00:20:30,399
Police? Has something happened?

306
00:20:30,415 --> 00:20:31,276
Oh, no!

307
00:20:31,646 --> 00:20:34,393
I’m an old friend of the Joestars.

308
00:20:35,293 --> 00:20:38,489
Although, I could hear Danny
whimper a moment ago...

309
00:20:38,595 --> 00:20:39,500
Ah, that was—

310
00:20:38,962 --> 00:20:41,373
-He came at me so suddenly.

311
00:20:41,791 --> 00:20:45,185
When I jumped in surprise,
I think my leg may have hit him!

312
00:20:45,228 --> 00:20:49,069
Danny is the Joestar household’s
wonderful guard dog.

313
00:20:49,655 --> 00:20:55,001
He’s a friendly creature, but
I’m sorry he surprised you.

314
00:20:55,755 --> 00:20:56,755
JoJo!

315
00:20:57,302 --> 00:20:59,979
You’ll let this Danny matter go, right?

316
00:21:01,498 --> 00:21:02,179
Yes, sir.

317
00:21:02,188 --> 00:21:03,026
Good.

318
00:21:03,763 --> 00:21:08,954
JoJo has lost his mother too—
and you both are the same age!

319
00:21:08,997 --> 00:21:11,132
Make sure to get along with each other.

320
00:21:12,085 --> 00:21:14,566
Now, allow me to show you to your room.

321
00:21:14,915 --> 00:21:15,915
Mister Brando!

322
00:21:19,399 --> 00:21:20,443
Nice to have met you!

323
00:21:23,966 --> 00:21:24,966
Ta-ta, JoJo!

324
00:21:33,272 --> 00:21:34,604
Now then, let me get—

325
00:21:34,684 --> 00:21:35,993
Watch it!

326
00:21:36,492 --> 00:21:38,360
Don’t touch my bag!

327
00:21:38,379 --> 00:21:39,502
I was just trying to carry it for—

328
00:21:39,539 --> 00:21:40,546
That’s enough.

329
00:21:42,021 --> 00:21:44,577
Your hand is covered in dog drool.

330
00:21:45,025 --> 00:21:47,505
Pardon me if I don’t want
it all over my things!

331
00:21:49,923 --> 00:21:53,222
Alright JoJo, I’ll tell
you from the get-go.

332
00:21:53,602 --> 00:21:56,102
I like being the best!
I’m always number one!

333
00:21:56,748 --> 00:21:59,232
I don’t care who you are,
no one looks down on me!

334
00:21:59,298 --> 00:22:01,481
I was only trying to be friendly!

335
00:22:01,705 --> 00:22:04,380
What are you two doing?

336
00:22:06,983 --> 00:22:08,491
And one more thing—

337
00:22:10,734 --> 00:22:12,822
I hate dogs.

338
00:22:13,725 --> 00:22:16,995
The way they grovel and suck
up to humans disgusts me.

339
00:22:17,103 --> 00:22:19,872
Keep your stupid dog away from me!

340
00:22:21,079 --> 00:22:23,135
Coming, Lord Joestar!

341
00:22:31,712 --> 00:22:36,712
Thus, with this meeting, the
two boys’ youth had begun.

342
00:22:56,979 --> 00:23:00,224
Are you coming, JoJo, Dio?

343
00:23:00,406 --> 00:23:08,145
<i>Bear in mind, as honourable nobles,</i>

344
00:23:08,386 --> 00:23:16,146
<i>We take on the duty of
becoming true gentlemen</i>

345
00:23:17,058 --> 00:23:21,056
<i>This is why we study, acquire knowledge,</i>

346
00:23:18,054 --> 00:23:19,754
{\an8}<i>(Without pause!)</i>

347
00:23:20,061 --> 00:23:21,761
{\an8}<i>(Without limit!)</i>

348
00:23:21,129 --> 00:23:24,145
<i>And arm ourselves with logic!</i>

349
00:23:23,081 --> 00:23:25,129
{\an8}<i>(So you’ll never lose!)</i>

350
00:23:25,177 --> 00:23:27,199
<i>Under the guidance of
the goddess of familial love</i>

351
00:23:27,240 --> 00:23:31,990
<i>For the sake of heading
the house of Joestar</i>

352
00:23:31,223 --> 00:23:33,459
{\an8}<i>(The honourable Joestars!)</i>

353
00:23:32,362 --> 00:23:36,754
<i>What’s this, JoJo? JoJo!</i>

354
00:23:36,803 --> 00:23:40,773
<i>The same mistakes once again</i>

355
00:23:40,816 --> 00:23:44,052
<i>How many times have
you made them! Six times!</i>

356
00:23:45,007 --> 00:23:49,408
<i>Dio has all of them correct!</i>

357
00:23:49,916 --> 00:23:52,329
It’s just because I love reading so much!

358
00:23:52,358 --> 00:23:54,857
But they haven’t even
taught us this in school yet!

359
00:24:03,017 --> 00:24:11,097
<i>Bear in mind, as proud nobles,</i>

360
00:24:11,188 --> 00:24:18,749
<i>We behave like true gentlemen</i>

361
00:24:19,757 --> 00:24:23,914
<i>Sit up straight, use your knife with grace,</i>

362
00:24:20,787 --> 00:24:22,755
{\an8}<i>(So elegantly!)</i>

363
00:24:22,800 --> 00:24:24,530
{\an8}<i>(So gracefully!)</i>

364
00:24:23,993 --> 00:24:27,771
<i>So that your mouth always remains spotless</i>

365
00:24:26,331 --> 00:24:27,731
{\an8}<i>(Unfailingly!)</i>

366
00:24:27,876 --> 00:24:29,874
<i>Under the guidance of
the goddess of familial love</i>

367
00:24:29,914 --> 00:24:34,556
<i>For the sake of being loved as a Joestar!</i>

368
00:24:33,946 --> 00:24:36,462
{\an8}<i>(The proud Joestars!)</i>

369
00:24:34,982 --> 00:24:39,031
<i>What’s this, JoJo? JoJo!</i>

370
00:24:39,519 --> 00:24:43,519
<i>Do you call yourself a gentleman?</i>

371
00:24:43,565 --> 00:24:47,541
<i>Look at Dio’s elegant touch</i>

372
00:24:47,589 --> 00:24:51,689
<i>His manners are perfect!</i>

373
00:24:52,315 --> 00:24:56,236
<i>Take away JoJo’s plates!
You will go without dinner tonight!</i>

374
00:24:56,276 --> 00:24:59,236
<i>Observe and follow Dio’s example</i>

375
00:24:59,780 --> 00:25:08,908
<i>I am embarrassed by
how much I’ve spoiled you</i>

376
00:25:09,000 --> 00:25:10,000
But...

377
00:25:10,360 --> 00:25:14,734
My mother taught me well. She
always made sure I sat up straight.

378
00:25:17,898 --> 00:25:24,936
<i>Bear in mind, as honourable nobles,</i>

379
00:25:25,263 --> 00:25:34,257
<i>In our hearts we must always consider
questions of philosophy and justice</i>

380
00:25:35,896 --> 00:25:39,975
In our great England, a tale of two knights
has been passed down for generations.

381
00:25:40,028 --> 00:25:44,882
One day, their master was
taken prisoner by the enemy.

382
00:25:45,678 --> 00:25:50,645
The enemy was afraid of the
two knights, who had great power.

383
00:25:50,683 --> 00:25:52,236
And so she gave them this condition:

384
00:25:53,590 --> 00:26:00,730
“If you two will be executed in her place,
I will guarantee the life of your master.”

385
00:26:02,392 --> 00:26:04,469
Here is my question for you:

386
00:26:04,739 --> 00:26:05,739
-Yes, sir!
-Yes, sir!

387
00:26:06,506 --> 00:26:13,155
Those two knights who gave themselves
up as prisoners to save their master;

388
00:26:14,127 --> 00:26:17,847
What was the first thing they
saw through their prison bars?

389
00:26:18,272 --> 00:26:21,445
Was it the mud that lay before their eyes?

390
00:26:22,051 --> 00:26:27,440
Or was it the stars shining above them?

391
00:26:28,269 --> 00:26:30,022
What do you think?

392
00:26:31,163 --> 00:26:32,263
The stars?

393
00:26:33,331 --> 00:26:34,431
Or the mud?

394
00:26:36,598 --> 00:26:37,598
I...

395
00:26:40,502 --> 00:26:42,354
I think they were looking at the mud.

396
00:26:44,099 --> 00:26:45,754
What’s your reasoning?

397
00:26:46,621 --> 00:26:52,046
In the end, they had no choice
but to die for their master.

398
00:26:52,999 --> 00:26:56,070
You can’t achieve anything if you’re dead.

399
00:26:56,103 --> 00:26:58,728
So no matter what tricks
they would have had to pull,

400
00:26:58,796 --> 00:27:00,869
I think they should have stayed
alive and done something!

401
00:27:00,925 --> 00:27:01,925
I think...

402
00:27:03,287 --> 00:27:05,057
They were looking at the stars!

403
00:27:05,615 --> 00:27:07,426
They held onto their honour!

404
00:27:07,452 --> 00:27:09,973
The names of those two knights
will be etched into history!

405
00:27:10,002 --> 00:27:11,202
So what!

406
00:27:12,112 --> 00:27:13,312
So what?

407
00:27:16,434 --> 00:27:20,069
The way one lives, and the things
one does, those are important!

408
00:27:20,098 --> 00:27:21,398
But they—

409
00:27:22,341 --> 00:27:25,677
They were left empty-handed
in the end!

410
00:27:25,997 --> 00:27:27,297
Such regret...

411
00:27:28,350 --> 00:27:29,650
Such powerlessness...

412
00:27:30,678 --> 00:27:32,292
What they saw was the mud!

413
00:27:32,995 --> 00:27:36,590
Their lesson is to teach us what
we can achieve by staying alive!

414
00:27:36,623 --> 00:27:38,488
They held onto their
pride until the very end!

415
00:27:38,517 --> 00:27:41,490
They were looking at the stars! I think
they’re teaching us <i>how</i> we should live!

416
00:27:41,514 --> 00:27:42,614
Listen!

417
00:27:43,537 --> 00:27:46,116
You’re a noble! You have it all!

418
00:27:46,142 --> 00:27:47,947
You’ve lived by taking
from those beneath you!

419
00:27:48,346 --> 00:27:53,560
So isn’t it your responsibility to think
about what you’ll achieve with your life?

420
00:27:53,661 --> 00:27:54,296
I—

421
00:27:54,315 --> 00:27:56,711
That’s enough, you two.

422
00:27:58,115 --> 00:28:01,624
There’s no right answer to this question.

423
00:28:02,408 --> 00:28:03,541
Bear in mind—

424
00:28:04,295 --> 00:28:08,761
<i>All people live in a prison called fate</i>

425
00:28:08,891 --> 00:28:12,995
<i>Reaching out through those bars,</i>

426
00:28:13,369 --> 00:28:17,827
<i>Do they see the stars? Or the mud?</i>

427
00:28:17,948 --> 00:28:23,317
<i>Either one could be said to be correct</i>

428
00:28:50,996 --> 00:28:53,343
<i>A world without disparity, that’s sports</i>

429
00:28:53,370 --> 00:28:55,704
<i>Where courage alone
has the chance to overturn</i>

430
00:28:55,734 --> 00:28:58,639
<i>Get ready to rumble! Fanaticism
overcomes all differences</i>

431
00:28:58,852 --> 00:29:02,240
<i>This is straight up religion!
If you lose, instant fucking funeral!</i>

432
00:29:02,298 --> 00:29:04,584
<i>All eyes on are on this ritual
where triumph goes to the victor</i>

433
00:29:04,632 --> 00:29:06,368
<i>Everyone, gather around!</i>

434
00:29:06,415 --> 00:29:08,391
<i>The winner is a sweeping hero</i>

435
00:29:08,476 --> 00:29:10,159
<i>Who will be declared king?!</i>

436
00:29:10,179 --> 00:29:11,926
<i>The opening bell rings</i>

437
00:29:11,952 --> 00:29:14,610
<i>Here comes today’s challenger!</i>

438
00:29:16,547 --> 00:29:17,047
Oi!

439
00:29:17,752 --> 00:29:19,625
Hey hey, JoJo JoJo!

440
00:29:33,315 --> 00:29:36,386
Right in the face! The winner is Joestar!

441
00:29:36,414 --> 00:29:38,169
Our new champion!

442
00:29:38,188 --> 00:29:39,537
You did it, JoJo!

443
00:29:39,555 --> 00:29:41,196
Danny would be proud!

444
00:29:41,233 --> 00:29:45,698
Now, who will be the next to
challenge our champion, JoJo?

445
00:29:45,734 --> 00:29:47,357
Is there anyone?

446
00:29:47,387 --> 00:29:49,331
Everyone listen up!

447
00:29:49,372 --> 00:29:54,372
A new face has just asked to join our game.

448
00:29:54,534 --> 00:29:57,670
His name is Dio Brando!

449
00:29:58,000 --> 00:29:59,737
Dio Brando?

450
00:29:58,589 --> 00:30:03,542
-Shall we tell our new friend
how we do things here?

451
00:30:03,739 --> 00:30:05,095
Yeah! Do it!

452
00:30:05,117 --> 00:30:07,540
Alright, let’s do it!

453
00:30:06,880 --> 00:30:07,580
-Good!

454
00:30:07,621 --> 00:30:10,177
The rule is if you get
hit in the face once, you—

455
00:30:10,207 --> 00:30:12,707
Don’t worry, I played by the
 same rules back in London.

456
00:30:12,738 --> 00:30:15,517
That’s the bell!

457
00:30:13,992 --> 00:30:15,530
-Go, JoJo!

458
00:30:15,549 --> 00:30:17,077
Beat him up!

459
00:30:17,796 --> 00:30:19,227
What is this move!

460
00:30:19,268 --> 00:30:20,683
I’ve never seen it before!

461
00:30:20,723 --> 00:30:21,961
Oi, JoJo!

462
00:30:37,423 --> 00:30:40,248
That’s a hit to the face!

463
00:30:40,271 --> 00:30:41,271
He lost!

464
00:30:43,075 --> 00:30:45,845
Our king! Our king!

465
00:30:45,875 --> 00:30:48,375
Dio! Dio! Dio! Dio!

466
00:30:48,425 --> 00:30:50,154
My eye!

467
00:30:50,174 --> 00:30:51,921
Guys, guys, guys!

468
00:30:53,995 --> 00:30:58,241
I think my finger went in his eye.

469
00:30:59,070 --> 00:31:02,691
I must forfeit my win. I have
to leave now, excuse me!

470
00:31:02,420 --> 00:31:02,926
-Hey, hey!

471
00:31:02,953 --> 00:31:07,198
Dio, you were amazing!
How do you move like that?

472
00:31:07,324 --> 00:31:09,403
Teach me!

473
00:31:10,084 --> 00:31:11,768
Guys! Ow...

474
00:31:18,125 --> 00:31:19,265
Danny...

475
00:31:22,061 --> 00:31:27,006
Why is Dio always trying to bring me down?

476
00:31:29,390 --> 00:31:31,746
It feels like he’s invading my life.

477
00:31:37,217 --> 00:31:40,987
<i>Hey, Danny, my heart aches</i>

478
00:31:43,548 --> 00:31:46,767
<i>And I’m filled with worry</i>

479
00:31:49,951 --> 00:31:55,726
<i>What if I were to die today?</i>

480
00:31:56,355 --> 00:32:01,568
<i>Would anyone cry for me?</i>

481
00:32:02,772 --> 00:32:07,505
<i>You’re always so understanding</i>

482
00:32:09,657 --> 00:32:14,129
<i>Thank you for staying by my side!</i>

483
00:32:15,525 --> 00:32:21,513
<i>If mum were still here,
would it feel this way?</i>

484
00:32:21,901 --> 00:32:27,957
<i>Would she love me this way?</i>

485
00:32:35,551 --> 00:32:36,551
You’re...

486
00:32:48,503 --> 00:32:50,049
My hanky...

487
00:32:52,478 --> 00:32:54,962
Oi! Thanks for bringing
my handkerchief back!

488
00:32:54,991 --> 00:32:57,603
Hey, I’ll be back here tomorrow too,

489
00:32:57,654 --> 00:32:59,553
So stop by again!

490
00:32:59,593 --> 00:33:00,450
Danny!

491
00:33:14,955 --> 00:33:16,604
Has it caught your fancy?

492
00:33:18,595 --> 00:33:20,911
Please excuse me for
grabbing it without permission.

493
00:33:21,102 --> 00:33:22,315
It’s alright.

494
00:33:23,254 --> 00:33:28,473
They say this Stone Mask was
unearthed in some Mexican ruins.

495
00:33:28,951 --> 00:33:29,951
Mexico...

496
00:33:29,972 --> 00:33:30,939
Mm-hmm.

497
00:33:31,782 --> 00:33:37,527
We bought it from a London art dealer,
around the time JoJo was born.

498
00:33:38,672 --> 00:33:41,896
On the way back,
we had a carriage accident.

499
00:33:42,853 --> 00:33:45,880
That was the time your dear
father saved us, you know.

500
00:33:48,483 --> 00:33:50,611
Are you interested in it?

501
00:33:51,440 --> 00:33:53,778
Oh, no. Not especially.

502
00:33:56,104 --> 00:33:57,098
Uh...

503
00:33:58,620 --> 00:34:01,729
JoJo is always out playing
with Danny, isn’t he?

504
00:34:02,432 --> 00:34:08,081
It’s because of the trust and
friendship Danny has in JoJo.

505
00:34:08,552 --> 00:34:10,694
Friendship? With a dog?

506
00:34:11,859 --> 00:34:16,593
I had bought Danny when JoJo was young.

507
00:34:17,606 --> 00:34:22,526
At first, he was afraid
of unfamiliar people,

508
00:34:22,712 --> 00:34:25,374
And he didn’t get on well with JoJo yet.

509
00:34:27,141 --> 00:34:31,843
But one time, JoJo was drowning in a river.

510
00:34:34,359 --> 00:34:38,294
There wasn’t even one person
around who could hear his voice.

511
00:34:39,713 --> 00:34:41,919
Just when JoJo was about to drown...

512
00:34:41,955 --> 00:34:46,089
A figure, hearing his screams,
flew down to the river.

513
00:34:46,119 --> 00:34:47,131
It was Danny!

514
00:34:48,281 --> 00:34:52,469
He dove in and saved JoJo’s life.

515
00:34:54,526 --> 00:35:00,129
Danny was brave to have risked
his own life to save another.

516
00:35:01,514 --> 00:35:09,224
Young JoJo was moved by Danny’s bravery.

517
00:35:10,970 --> 00:35:14,873
That’s when JoJo truly
became friends with him.

518
00:35:15,738 --> 00:35:16,682
Is that so?

519
00:35:16,716 --> 00:35:17,462
M’lord.

520
00:35:17,481 --> 00:35:19,954
Eh? Ah, that’s right.

521
00:35:25,966 --> 00:35:27,966
Friends...

522
00:35:31,273 --> 00:35:32,432
Erina!

523
00:35:32,443 --> 00:35:33,237
JoJo!

524
00:35:33,269 --> 00:35:35,269
The two met once more!

525
00:35:35,972 --> 00:35:40,463
Love! That wonderful curiosity
that guided JoJo’s actions.

526
00:35:40,511 --> 00:35:44,317
JoJo was instantly
head over heels for her.

527
00:35:46,119 --> 00:35:47,119
Danny!

528
00:35:47,724 --> 00:35:48,764
Come boy!

529
00:35:52,644 --> 00:35:57,204
Oh, you’re so clever to eat
the fruit but not the core.

530
00:35:59,024 --> 00:36:01,492
Hey JoJo, what are you carving over there?

531
00:36:01,526 --> 00:36:04,626
Huh? It’s nothing.

532
00:36:04,652 --> 00:36:05,859
What are you hiding?

533
00:36:05,898 --> 00:36:07,461
It’s nothing interesting.

534
00:36:07,481 --> 00:36:09,314
When you say it like that, it makes
me want to see it even more!

535
00:36:09,331 --> 00:36:10,514
You’ll just laugh!

536
00:36:10,529 --> 00:36:11,966
I won’t laugh.

537
00:36:12,048 --> 00:36:12,945
You’ll tell people!

538
00:36:12,957 --> 00:36:14,171
I won’t tell, so show me!

539
00:36:14,185 --> 00:36:15,304
I told you, no!

540
00:36:15,319 --> 00:36:16,504
JoJo!

541
00:36:19,102 --> 00:36:20,102
Oh, my!

542
00:36:20,473 --> 00:36:28,004
<i>Erina, just saying your
name makes me feel at ease</i>

543
00:36:28,562 --> 00:36:36,450
<i>Any musician would fall
in love with its melody</i>

544
00:36:37,028 --> 00:36:40,359
<i>It puts me in such a good mood</i>

545
00:36:40,407 --> 00:36:41,188
Oh!

546
00:36:41,235 --> 00:36:44,301
<i>To be laughing like this</i>

547
00:36:45,245 --> 00:36:52,445
<i>There’s nothing but blue skies
here in vibrant Liverpool</i>

548
00:36:52,786 --> 00:36:54,459
<i>Erina</i>

549
00:36:54,777 --> 00:36:56,394
<i>JoJo</i>

550
00:36:57,139 --> 00:37:00,468
<i>Our happiness is right here</i>

551
00:37:00,530 --> 00:37:08,038
<i>The clouds are proud, and
the wind’s a little sweet</i>

552
00:37:08,977 --> 00:37:10,671
<i>JoJo</i>

553
00:37:10,969 --> 00:37:12,830
<i>Erina</i>

554
00:37:13,537 --> 00:37:16,705
<i>There aren’t enough words</i>

555
00:37:16,763 --> 00:37:23,657
<i>For these ever overflowing feelings</i>

556
00:37:25,109 --> 00:37:33,215
<i>I want to hear your voice
say, “it makes me happy”</i>

557
00:37:33,487 --> 00:37:38,270
<i>That would be so
embarrassing, you—</i>

558
00:37:39,030 --> 00:37:40,769
<i>Scoundrel!</i>

559
00:37:41,841 --> 00:37:48,748
<i>I don’t know why, but I’m drawn to you</i>

560
00:37:49,889 --> 00:37:57,389
<i>Then find a reason,
let’s make it our reason!</i>

561
00:37:57,530 --> 00:37:59,477
<i>Your hand,</i>

562
00:37:59,524 --> 00:38:01,536
<i>My hand,</i>

563
00:38:02,053 --> 00:38:04,973
<i>When they’re apart I feel so lost</i>

564
00:38:05,189 --> 00:38:12,844
<i>It gives me a little courage
to move forward to tomorrow</i>

565
00:38:13,688 --> 00:38:21,716
<i>Our hearts are resonating,
beating in time</i>

566
00:38:21,853 --> 00:38:31,835
<i>Drawing us together, these
fleeting feelings surround us</i>

567
00:38:35,994 --> 00:38:37,185
It’s already this late!

568
00:38:38,145 --> 00:38:40,788
We have a guest coming
tonight, I have to hurry home.

569
00:38:41,649 --> 00:38:42,649
Erina!

570
00:38:42,838 --> 00:38:43,838
I’ll see you tomorrow!

571
00:38:44,373 --> 00:38:45,635
Yes, JoJo!

572
00:38:45,647 --> 00:38:46,502
Danny!

573
00:38:50,110 --> 00:38:58,070
<i>The one I’m so strongly
drawn to, his name is...</i>

574
00:38:58,162 --> 00:39:06,073
<i>Jonathan Joestar</i>

575
00:39:13,247 --> 00:39:14,247
Hey!

576
00:39:16,407 --> 00:39:18,121
You’re Erina Pendleton, right?

577
00:39:19,483 --> 00:39:24,280
I heard you were hanging
out with JoJo today.

578
00:39:25,078 --> 00:39:26,078
Umm...

579
00:39:26,372 --> 00:39:27,472
What do you...

580
00:39:57,103 --> 00:39:57,928
He...

581
00:39:57,942 --> 00:39:59,490
He did it!

582
00:39:59,533 --> 00:40:01,144
That’s our Dio!

583
00:40:01,172 --> 00:40:04,505
He does the things we’re too chicken
to, and with such confidence too!

584
00:40:04,547 --> 00:40:08,398
I’ve got goosebumps!
I want to be just like him!

585
00:40:12,048 --> 00:40:14,220
Have you kissed JoJo yet?

586
00:40:16,749 --> 00:40:18,107
You haven’t, have you?

587
00:40:20,675 --> 00:40:23,858
The first person you kissed wasn’t JoJo...

588
00:40:23,886 --> 00:40:25,497
It was me, Dio!

589
00:40:26,658 --> 00:40:31,319
You know what this sort of thing
means for a lady’s reputation, right?

590
00:40:34,342 --> 00:40:35,064
Hey!

591
00:40:35,086 --> 00:40:36,704
She’s—!

592
00:40:36,734 --> 00:40:38,569
You bitch!

593
00:40:39,305 --> 00:40:42,015
What are you doing washing
my kiss away with mud?!

594
00:40:52,186 --> 00:40:55,629
<i>Dio...</i>

595
00:40:56,631 --> 00:41:00,747
<i>Dio...</i>

596
00:41:01,107 --> 00:41:02,949
Get up, bitch!

597
00:41:02,975 --> 00:41:05,705
What’re you sleeping for?

598
00:41:06,143 --> 00:41:09,445
Oi, why’s the booze gone?!

599
00:41:09,489 --> 00:41:13,817
Who do you think puts
food on the table? Stupid bitch!

600
00:41:13,865 --> 00:41:16,048
Hey, now go buy some booze!

601
00:41:16,077 --> 00:41:18,942
Father, mother’s clearly not well!

602
00:41:18,976 --> 00:41:21,954
She’s just fakin’ it!

603
00:41:22,375 --> 00:41:24,263
Oi, you hear me?

604
00:41:23,111 --> 00:41:24,611
-Stop it, Father!

605
00:41:24,805 --> 00:41:26,281
Mum! Mum!

606
00:41:26,318 --> 00:41:28,524
I’m sorry! Please forgive me!

607
00:41:28,553 --> 00:41:31,189
Of course you shouldn’t go to the shops!

608
00:41:31,339 --> 00:41:36,595
I’ve hurt you. I’m a good-for-nothin’.
Please forgive me!

609
00:41:36,762 --> 00:41:39,887
In tough times like these, I’ve
gotta work for your sake too.

610
00:41:39,920 --> 00:41:42,412
Please, you’ve got to get well!

611
00:41:45,138 --> 00:41:49,082
<i>Dio...</i>

612
00:41:49,587 --> 00:41:53,815
<i>Can’t you hear my voice?</i>

613
00:41:51,112 --> 00:41:53,455
-Mum! Mum!

614
00:41:53,960 --> 00:41:57,247
<i>The voice calling for you?</i>

615
00:41:58,063 --> 00:42:01,113
Dio boy, go and buy me booze!

616
00:42:01,366 --> 00:42:02,788
But our money’s already—

617
00:42:02,835 --> 00:42:05,067
Are you talking back?!

618
00:42:05,130 --> 00:42:07,096
You got money from that
factory job, don’t ya?

619
00:42:07,125 --> 00:42:10,250
Please, leave some money
for medicine at least!

620
00:42:10,288 --> 00:42:12,335
You’re really gonna
disobey me, you bastard?

621
00:42:12,376 --> 00:42:12,945
Father!

622
00:42:12,971 --> 00:42:16,705
You really expect me to
work my arse off for you? Idiot!

623
00:42:18,548 --> 00:42:21,837
You’re all trying to make a fool of me!

624
00:42:21,988 --> 00:42:24,977
After all the trouble I went
through to nick that noble’s shit!

625
00:42:25,287 --> 00:42:27,908
That’s it. That noble, Joestar.

626
00:42:27,936 --> 00:42:30,146
Why don’t I send him a letter...

627
00:42:30,441 --> 00:42:31,651
No...

628
00:42:32,995 --> 00:42:35,527
You and I are different!

629
00:42:38,196 --> 00:42:41,378
<i>Dio...</i>

630
00:42:42,543 --> 00:42:46,338
<i>Dio...</i>

631
00:42:46,981 --> 00:42:48,997
<i>Dio...</i>

632
00:42:49,079 --> 00:42:50,148
Dio!!

633
00:42:50,779 --> 00:42:53,937
<i>Dio...</i>

634
00:42:55,974 --> 00:43:01,982
<i>Dio, how could you do such a thing?
How could you hurt her like that!</i>

635
00:43:02,164 --> 00:43:08,164
<i>What in the world have I ever done
to you?! Can you tell me, Dio?</i>

636
00:43:08,580 --> 00:43:12,848
<i>You’re so amazing, so
much more than I am</i>

637
00:43:12,881 --> 00:43:14,233
I admired you!

638
00:43:14,988 --> 00:43:21,275
<i>But now there is a single
flame that burns in my heart</i>

639
00:43:22,590 --> 00:43:23,590
Dio!

640
00:43:27,966 --> 00:43:30,978
<i>Aren’t you using my name</i>

641
00:43:31,008 --> 00:43:33,050
<i>DIO: A little too lightly?
JOJO: I’ll never forgive you!</i>

642
00:43:33,086 --> 00:43:37,243
<i>So you’ve heard? What I
did to your beloved Erina?</i>

643
00:43:35,503 --> 00:43:37,257
-You’ve disgraced her!

644
00:43:37,341 --> 00:43:40,818
DIO: I bet you’re mad with jealousy!
<i>JOJO: This is for her sake, not mine!</i>

645
00:43:46,862 --> 00:43:52,379
<i>I have to stand up to him, even
if I can’t beat him. I cannot lose!</i>

646
00:43:53,479 --> 00:43:59,201
<i>Control your emotions, you’re
different from that drunken lout</i>

647
00:43:59,741 --> 00:44:05,408
<i>On the blood resonating in my heart,
I swear to restore her honour, Dio! </i>

648
00:44:06,045 --> 00:44:12,026
<i>I’ll put you back in your place,
I’ll teach you a lesson you won’t forget</i>

649
00:44:14,811 --> 00:44:15,391
Come at me!

650
00:44:15,877 --> 00:44:18,849
<i>This new power arising within me</i>

651
00:44:19,096 --> 00:44:20,580
It feels so good!

652
00:44:28,433 --> 00:44:32,153
<i>You’re the one who lit this fire in me</i>

653
00:44:33,042 --> 00:44:34,042
Dio!

654
00:44:35,005 --> 00:44:43,605
<i>I won’t stop beating you until you cry!</i>

655
00:44:47,771 --> 00:44:51,041
<i>How dare you do this to me?</i>

656
00:44:51,076 --> 00:44:53,833
<i>You miserable insect!</i>

657
00:44:54,270 --> 00:44:56,942
<i>You scum of the earth!</i>

658
00:44:57,381 --> 00:45:03,697
<i>How dare such scum like
you come at me, Dio!</i>

659
00:45:03,764 --> 00:45:08,873
<i>Me, the great Dio!</i>

660
00:45:12,537 --> 00:45:14,408
What on earth is going on?!

661
00:45:15,485 --> 00:45:19,070
You two! You’ll be punished for this!
Now go back to your rooms!

662
00:45:32,001 --> 00:45:33,001
Dio...

663
00:45:33,740 --> 00:45:36,801
That stupid kiss of yours hurt
me more than you intended!

664
00:45:42,326 --> 00:45:43,594
Ah... Eri—

665
00:45:47,351 --> 00:45:49,663
I feel so miserable!

666
00:45:51,994 --> 00:45:54,210
I’ve never felt pain like this before...

667
00:45:54,245 --> 00:45:55,245
Erina!

668
00:45:56,347 --> 00:46:01,628
Erina! Did you say goodbye
to all your friends?

669
00:46:04,190 --> 00:46:05,390
Yes, Father.

670
00:46:06,021 --> 00:46:10,045
I’m sorry for imposing my career
on you. Even though I know you—

671
00:46:10,074 --> 00:46:11,074
Let’s go.

672
00:46:12,127 --> 00:46:13,974
I’ll make friends over there too.

673
00:46:19,642 --> 00:46:20,642
Erina...

674
00:46:21,688 --> 00:46:23,823
I underestimated JoJo.

675
00:46:25,510 --> 00:46:27,637
His explosive power...

676
00:46:28,899 --> 00:46:30,577
His resilience...

677
00:46:31,621 --> 00:46:33,679
I have to become stronger...

678
00:46:35,122 --> 00:46:37,257
So that I can become
a gentleman at heart!

679
00:46:38,020 --> 00:46:41,770
I have to control my anger and stay calm...

680
00:46:44,268 --> 00:46:46,337
So that I can take everything from him!

681
00:47:05,486 --> 00:47:06,524
However...

682
00:47:16,006 --> 00:47:17,069
What’s that noise?

683
00:47:20,027 --> 00:47:22,150
Could someone be
inside the incinerator?

684
00:47:23,336 --> 00:47:24,919
Are they trying to get out?!

685
00:47:25,411 --> 00:47:26,411
Ah, it burns!

686
00:47:31,094 --> 00:47:32,094
Danny!!

687
00:47:32,487 --> 00:47:33,535
Oh my god...

688
00:47:33,579 --> 00:47:35,848
Someone! Someone please help!

689
00:48:14,529 --> 00:48:16,003
<i>Seven years passed from that day</i>

690
00:48:16,027 --> 00:48:18,649
<i>Times are changing,
the Victorian era’s flying by us</i>

691
00:48:18,678 --> 00:48:20,900
<i>Population increasing to
the point of overflowing</i>

692
00:48:20,927 --> 00:48:23,181
<i>Art and entertainment
are showered in praise</i>

693
00:48:23,211 --> 00:48:26,063
<i>In the middle of this
unstoppable flow, agitation rages</i>

694
00:48:26,095 --> 00:48:28,595
<i>The height of development,
the growth of British culture</i>

695
00:48:28,623 --> 00:48:30,811
<i>But what goes up, must come
down. It’s only natural</i>

696
00:48:30,836 --> 00:48:32,727
<i>That the top runners are being singled out</i>

697
00:48:32,781 --> 00:48:34,757
<i>London’s peace has one
of its fingers broken</i>

698
00:48:34,780 --> 00:48:36,739
<i>Chaotic days mix the old and the new</i>

699
00:48:36,763 --> 00:48:38,739
<i>The map of London
paints a stark contrast</i>

700
00:48:38,763 --> 00:48:40,930
<i>Just like the current state of the country</i>

701
00:48:40,952 --> 00:48:42,674
<i>Put the focus on the
dark parts and you’ll see</i>

702
00:48:42,697 --> 00:48:44,887
<i>The curtain of swaying inequality</i>

703
00:48:44,912 --> 00:48:46,917
<i>In this market still
learning from its past!</i>

704
00:48:47,624 --> 00:48:51,250
You’re... You’re certain,
that it was the Stone Mask?

705
00:48:51,279 --> 00:48:52,569
The one excavated from Mexico?

706
00:48:52,611 --> 00:48:54,173
From Mexico, you say?

707
00:48:54,216 --> 00:48:55,931
It was quite a while ago...

708
00:48:55,958 --> 00:48:58,686
A while?! Could you please clarify?

709
00:48:59,275 --> 00:49:01,562
Yes, I’m <i>certain</i>, sir.

710
00:49:01,596 --> 00:49:04,889
Some gentleman’s wife
fell in love with it,

711
00:49:04,943 --> 00:49:06,803
And bought it from me at a high price—

712
00:49:06,830 --> 00:49:09,638
Yes!! Finally! I found it!

713
00:49:09,673 --> 00:49:11,415
Now, where could I find this gentleman—

714
00:49:11,434 --> 00:49:12,434
Wait a minute!

715
00:49:12,809 --> 00:49:14,134
I don’t trust you...

716
00:49:14,444 --> 00:49:16,741
Who the hell are you anyway?

717
00:49:16,835 --> 00:49:21,890
I apologise. My name
is Zeppeli, and I’m a baron.

718
00:49:21,934 --> 00:49:24,436
I came from Italy to
 find the Stone Mask.

719
00:49:24,459 --> 00:49:25,604
All the way from Italy?!

720
00:49:25,615 --> 00:49:26,282
Yes.

721
00:49:26,321 --> 00:49:28,416
Wait, he said he was
a nobleman from up north...

722
00:49:28,441 --> 00:49:30,560
I’ll go check in the books!

723
00:49:30,578 --> 00:49:31,578
Thank you.

724
00:49:33,667 --> 00:49:36,074
Just a little word of warning...

725
00:49:36,397 --> 00:49:38,447
The sun will be setting soon.

726
00:49:39,140 --> 00:49:41,786
It’s better if you don’t
go beyond that street.

727
00:49:46,042 --> 00:49:48,537
A fog has rolled in...

728
00:49:49,742 --> 00:49:53,700
<i>(A palpable shadow stretches over the city)
</i>

729
00:49:53,742 --> 00:49:57,171
<i>(And soon it’ll swallow the sun whole)</i>

730
00:49:57,416 --> 00:50:05,224
<i>(Don’t let it get you,
fight as hard as you can!)</i>

731
00:50:05,315 --> 00:50:13,145
<i>(Fog and smog cover the city,
hiding the smell of crime)</i>

732
00:50:13,231 --> 00:50:19,994
<i>(Stretch out your hands towards the light)</i>

733
00:50:20,334 --> 00:50:22,199
<i>(We won’t sink down to hell!)</i>

734
00:50:25,627 --> 00:50:33,272
<i>The filth rubs off on the clean
and gathers like grime</i>

735
00:50:33,524 --> 00:50:37,350
<i>Thrown away with the rubbish</i>

736
00:50:37,394 --> 00:50:41,050
<i>Pressed together, our
lot gives off a stench</i>

737
00:50:41,093 --> 00:50:44,784
<i>The sweet smell of darkness</i>

738
00:50:44,826 --> 00:50:48,435
<i>Is comforting to us</i>

739
00:50:48,961 --> 00:50:56,587
<i>(Something’s wrong, people
 are thirsty, distorted, broken!)</i>

740
00:50:56,674 --> 00:51:04,015
<i>(Jack the Ripper has drawn first blood!)</i>

741
00:51:04,557 --> 00:51:12,100
<i>(Hate the poor, hate the
rich, and raise your voice)</i>

742
00:51:12,377 --> 00:51:19,002
<i>(Gather here and now, Jacks of this town!)</i>

743
00:51:19,535 --> 00:51:21,416
<i>(Rebellion is now!)</i>

744
00:51:24,295 --> 00:51:26,970
<i>In 1887, in Trafalgar Square</i>

745
00:51:26,994 --> 00:51:28,487
<i>(We raise our voices!)</i>

746
00:51:28,512 --> 00:51:31,277
<i>(Give us equality! Work! And money!)</i>

747
00:51:32,537 --> 00:51:34,375
<i>The rich in their ivory towers</i>

748
00:51:34,398 --> 00:51:36,314
<i>(They look on at us and laugh!)</i>

749
00:51:36,366 --> 00:51:39,465
<i>(Give us food! Every day! Let us live!)</i>

750
00:51:40,009 --> 00:51:43,311
<i>(The world is ever accelerating)</i>

751
00:51:43,382 --> 00:51:46,727
<i>Rebellion is stopped in its tracks,
blood floods the streets of London</i>

752
00:51:47,040 --> 00:51:50,365
<i>Away from there now, in Liverpool,
seven years have flown by</i>

753
00:51:50,392 --> 00:51:51,654
<i>Their graduation year</i>

754
00:51:51,676 --> 00:51:54,087
<i>Their graduation? But who are “they”?</i>

755
00:51:54,114 --> 00:51:56,195
<i>From inside the scrum
they head for victory</i>

756
00:51:56,229 --> 00:51:59,970
<i>So dazzling, brightly
shining, a pair of stars</i>

757
00:52:00,040 --> 00:52:08,090
<i>(Now is the time to raise our voices!)</i>

758
00:52:08,576 --> 00:52:09,829
He’s got it!

759
00:52:09,870 --> 00:52:15,750
The star of Hugh Hudson, our very
own Jonathan Joestar, grabs the pass!

760
00:52:17,084 --> 00:52:19,169
<i>(He’s like a heavy locomotive!)</i>

761
00:52:18,508 --> 00:52:19,608
{\an8}<i>(One’s on his back!)</i>

762
00:52:19,194 --> 00:52:21,374
<i>(He can’t be toppled)</i>

763
00:52:20,426 --> 00:52:21,526
{\an8}<i>(And a second!)</i>

764
00:52:21,405 --> 00:52:24,515
<i>(Keep pushing forward, JoJo!)</i>

765
00:52:23,102 --> 00:52:24,480
{\an8}<i>(Bloody hell!)</i>

766
00:52:24,554 --> 00:52:26,840
<i>(The pride of our school!)</i>

767
00:52:26,052 --> 00:52:27,052
{\an8}<i>(Incredible!)</i>

768
00:52:26,864 --> 00:52:28,783
<i>(Hugh Hudson’s acclaimed JoJo!)</i>

769
00:52:27,874 --> 00:52:28,953
{\an8}<i>(And a fourth!)</i>

770
00:52:28,807 --> 00:52:30,932
<i>(Is he finally wavering?)</i>

771
00:52:30,953 --> 00:52:32,385
{\an8}Someone caught the pass!

772
00:52:31,636 --> 00:52:34,418
<i>(None other than the great star Dio)</i>

773
00:52:33,627 --> 00:52:35,035
{\an8}<i>(Dio Brando)</i>

774
00:52:34,473 --> 00:52:35,822
<i>(Leaving them all behind)</i>

775
00:52:35,846 --> 00:52:38,486
<i>(Once again, Dio catches the pass)</i>

776
00:52:37,934 --> 00:52:39,516
{\an8}<i>(Nobody can catch up to him)</i>

777
00:52:39,474 --> 00:52:42,959
<i>(They move like clockwork! You’d
almost feel bad for their rivals!)</i>

778
00:52:43,021 --> 00:52:46,019
<i>(Our school’s pride!)</i>

779
00:52:45,904 --> 00:52:46,700
{\an8}<i>(Truly!)</i>

780
00:52:46,725 --> 00:52:50,193
<i>(JoJo and Dio!)</i>

781
00:52:50,239 --> 00:52:54,749
<i>(In perfect harmony, they
make the best partners!)</i>

782
00:52:54,797 --> 00:52:58,596
JoJo! Your pass won’t go to waste!

783
00:52:59,123 --> 00:53:00,385
Try!!

784
00:53:00,408 --> 00:53:02,977
The final match of the
season ends in victory!

785
00:53:02,995 --> 00:53:03,677
Dio!

786
00:53:03,686 --> 00:53:04,282
JoJo!

787
00:53:04,316 --> 00:53:05,631
That was magnificent!

788
00:53:05,653 --> 00:53:07,634
It was all thanks to your pass!

789
00:53:07,964 --> 00:53:11,184
Let’s go and tell Father
about it right away!

790
00:53:12,106 --> 00:53:12,932
Right, JoJo?

791
00:53:12,940 --> 00:53:13,599
Uh-huh.

792
00:53:13,657 --> 00:53:14,959
Dio!

793
00:53:15,013 --> 00:53:18,837
Can we write about your friendship
with JoJo for the school newspaper?

794
00:53:18,865 --> 00:53:19,865
Thanks!

795
00:53:20,822 --> 00:53:22,719
Let me get changed first.

796
00:53:22,735 --> 00:53:23,644
Shall we go home together?

797
00:53:23,680 --> 00:53:24,579
Yeah.

798
00:53:28,082 --> 00:53:33,521
<i>Time passed like the
endless flow of water</i>

799
00:53:34,185 --> 00:53:40,940
<i>Ever since you started
calling him “Father”</i>

800
00:53:42,315 --> 00:53:47,731
<i>I think of that word
which is so familiar to me</i>

801
00:53:48,530 --> 00:53:54,863
<i>Seven years spent studying diligently</i>

802
00:53:55,268 --> 00:54:02,002
<i>You’re... beautiful,
and a true gentleman</i>

803
00:54:02,811 --> 00:54:08,489
<i>My friend, who’s always
pushing me to be better</i>

804
00:54:09,261 --> 00:54:15,942
<i>You’ve repented for the
wrong you did to Erina</i>

805
00:54:16,402 --> 00:54:25,443
<i>You’ve offered me a shoulder
to lean on, now that Danny’s gone</i>

806
00:54:26,858 --> 00:54:32,073
<i>We walked this path
together for seven years</i>

807
00:54:32,127 --> 00:54:36,325
<i>I always followed in your
footsteps, one step behind,</i>

808
00:54:36,577 --> 00:54:48,352
<i>So why is it that I don’t
feel any friendship for you?</i>

809
00:55:05,363 --> 00:55:07,544
How are you feeling?

810
00:55:09,521 --> 00:55:14,323
Well, I’m old enough now that
a mere cold can last a long time.

811
00:55:14,362 --> 00:55:16,426
Sir, you’re not that old yet!

812
00:55:18,283 --> 00:55:22,085
Ah, well! I’ve got some big news for you!

813
00:55:22,124 --> 00:55:24,780
JoJo and Dio Brando, they...

814
00:55:24,965 --> 00:55:27,008
Seem to have won!

815
00:55:29,824 --> 00:55:35,559
Ah, Dio is a proper member
of the Joestar family now!

816
00:55:37,451 --> 00:55:40,717
And JoJo has become
a splendid gentleman.

817
00:55:40,757 --> 00:55:44,328
His recent archaeology thesis is superb!

818
00:55:44,831 --> 00:55:49,286
And Dio is projected to graduate
top of his class in law school.

819
00:55:50,020 --> 00:55:51,020
I...

820
00:55:51,579 --> 00:55:53,451
I admire you! Back then—

821
00:55:53,495 --> 00:55:54,513
My lord!

822
00:55:54,791 --> 00:55:55,179
Yes?

823
00:55:55,213 --> 00:55:56,508
I’m home!

824
00:55:56,930 --> 00:56:00,606
Dio! Welcome back!
Ah, and JoJo as well!

825
00:56:02,067 --> 00:56:03,067
Father!

826
00:56:03,386 --> 00:56:04,526
Are you alright?

827
00:56:05,985 --> 00:56:08,312
I can’t get rid of this cough...

828
00:56:08,940 --> 00:56:12,687
Today, the doctor recommended
I be admitted to hospital.

829
00:56:14,972 --> 00:56:16,272
I object!

830
00:56:18,701 --> 00:56:22,153
These days, hospitals
only care about profits!

831
00:56:22,602 --> 00:56:24,474
They say it’s a problem in London too.

832
00:56:25,525 --> 00:56:26,525
It’s true...

833
00:56:26,824 --> 00:56:29,193
I feel safer at home.

834
00:56:30,010 --> 00:56:31,247
I give in.

835
00:56:32,406 --> 00:56:37,043
The shaky hands and chest pain,
they’ll likely get better before long.

836
00:56:38,146 --> 00:56:41,415
Enough of that. You two...
Congratulations on your victory!

837
00:56:41,452 --> 00:56:41,822
What?!

838
00:56:41,860 --> 00:56:42,322
What?!

839
00:56:42,355 --> 00:56:43,385
You already know?

840
00:56:43,421 --> 00:56:44,454
How?

841
00:56:44,501 --> 00:56:47,383
Inspector Archer here told me.

842
00:56:47,664 --> 00:56:48,990
How rude of you, inspector!

843
00:56:49,005 --> 00:56:49,505
Huh?

844
00:56:50,351 --> 00:56:51,512
We...

845
00:56:52,487 --> 00:56:55,215
We wanted to see Father’s face light up...

846
00:56:55,826 --> 00:56:56,985
So we rushed home!

847
00:56:58,568 --> 00:57:00,653
Oh no, silly me!

848
00:57:02,319 --> 00:57:05,776
I truly am proud.

849
00:57:06,722 --> 00:57:10,214
I have such wonderful sons.

850
00:57:12,303 --> 00:57:14,039
Especially you, Dio.

851
00:57:14,591 --> 00:57:16,753
You’ve worked so very hard.

852
00:57:17,694 --> 00:57:21,550
Feel free to do whatever
you like after graduation.

853
00:57:23,115 --> 00:57:24,583
I was born poor...

854
00:57:25,293 --> 00:57:27,063
But you gave me a chance.

855
00:57:27,642 --> 00:57:28,880
Thank you.

856
00:57:30,852 --> 00:57:33,200
Well then, I’ll be off.

857
00:57:33,717 --> 00:57:36,563
Inspector, thank you for always visiting.

858
00:57:37,416 --> 00:57:41,202
I have a busy night ahead of me, with
the likes of Jack the Ripper out there.

859
00:57:41,239 --> 00:57:43,686
But this is Liverpool!

860
00:57:43,947 --> 00:57:48,736
There are men like him without
any humanity everywhere.

861
00:57:49,188 --> 00:57:50,914
Now, if you’ll pardon me.

862
00:58:16,346 --> 00:58:19,361
The spring mechanism only reacts to blood...

863
00:58:20,337 --> 00:58:21,637
Who on earth made this...

864
00:58:22,422 --> 00:58:23,573
And for what reason?

865
00:58:25,578 --> 00:58:29,451
If I solved this riddle, it might cause a
sensation in the archaeology department.

866
00:58:29,495 --> 00:58:33,192
If that happened, this mask that my
mother bought would have a fate of its own.

867
00:58:43,109 --> 00:58:44,109
This is...

868
00:58:46,523 --> 00:58:47,758
Dario Brando?

869
00:58:48,304 --> 00:58:50,717
Thank you again, Master Dio—

870
00:58:50,748 --> 00:58:53,518
Oh, it’s the least I could do.

871
00:58:53,583 --> 00:58:57,464
Thank you. I’m getting too old for this.

872
00:58:58,374 --> 00:59:00,166
“Right now... I’m sick.”

873
00:59:01,236 --> 00:59:02,768
“I’ll probably die.”

874
00:59:03,733 --> 00:59:05,140
“My heart hurts,”

875
00:59:05,706 --> 00:59:06,879
“My hands shake,”

876
00:59:08,306 --> 00:59:10,032
“And I can’t stop coughing.”

877
00:59:14,497 --> 00:59:18,526
<i>Dio...</i>

878
00:59:18,909 --> 00:59:22,880
<i>Dio...</i>

879
00:59:23,334 --> 00:59:27,705
<i>Can’t you hear my voice?</i>

880
00:59:27,758 --> 00:59:32,363
<i>The voice calling for you?</i>

881
00:59:32,751 --> 00:59:37,045
<i>Mum died and left me alone</i>

882
00:59:38,043 --> 00:59:41,241
<i>Yes, alone with that piece of shit!</i>

883
00:59:41,342 --> 00:59:45,920
<i>I endured no matter what</i>

884
00:59:47,079 --> 00:59:50,039
<i>Yes, until the day finally came</i>

885
00:59:50,087 --> 00:59:55,285
Bloody hell! Ever since that wench
died I’ve been crumbling in debt!

886
00:59:55,332 --> 00:59:56,549
I know!

887
00:59:56,849 --> 01:00:00,856
You pawn this crap and bring
me back some booze instead!

888
01:00:03,089 --> 01:00:07,813
<i>My one and only memento of mum</i>

889
01:00:07,854 --> 01:00:10,267
<i>You threw it away!
You wiped your feet with it!</i>

890
01:00:10,315 --> 01:00:11,974
I don’t bloody need it anymore!

891
01:00:12,014 --> 01:00:15,998
<i>He’s the one who killed mum</i>

892
01:00:16,039 --> 01:00:18,919
<i>Everything’s been
taken away from me</i>

893
01:00:18,976 --> 01:00:20,528
Are you bloody deaf, Dio?!

894
01:00:20,885 --> 01:00:28,442
<i>How hellish that your blood
is flowing through my veins</i>

895
01:00:29,947 --> 01:00:33,331
<i>I’ll bury you and this damn curse</i>

896
01:00:33,995 --> 01:00:36,810
<i>I will take everything
into my own two hands!</i>

897
01:00:38,943 --> 01:00:47,156
<i>I’ll stay on top, even to
the limits of my humanity</i>

898
01:00:47,748 --> 01:00:51,787
<i>I will find the resolve, plan ahead,</i>

899
01:00:53,219 --> 01:00:56,047
<i>And then, hiding behind a mask—</i>

900
01:00:56,082 --> 01:00:59,285
<i>Dario Brando, my wretched father</i>

901
01:00:59,856 --> 01:01:03,378
<i>May you rot in hell,
together with the past</i>

902
01:01:04,670 --> 01:01:07,792
<i>A world where everything is perfect,</i>

903
01:01:08,699 --> 01:01:12,513
<i>In the palm of your hand, Dio!</i>

904
01:01:22,328 --> 01:01:23,328
Dio!

905
01:01:24,626 --> 01:01:26,195
What’s that in your hand? Medicine?

906
01:01:28,878 --> 01:01:30,100
What’s the matter, JoJo?

907
01:01:30,121 --> 01:01:32,452
I found this letter from your
father, from seven years ago.

908
01:01:34,064 --> 01:01:37,889
It details your father’s symptoms
at the time of his death.

909
01:01:39,006 --> 01:01:40,006
Huh?

910
01:01:40,547 --> 01:01:41,698
Show me that.

911
01:01:42,479 --> 01:01:44,286
They’re the same symptoms as my father’s.

912
01:01:47,522 --> 01:01:49,752
Are you always the one who
brings Father his medicine?

913
01:01:50,955 --> 01:01:51,853
What is this non—

914
01:01:51,865 --> 01:01:52,865
Answer me!

915
01:01:53,916 --> 01:01:55,829
What on earth are
you trying to say?!

916
01:01:55,851 --> 01:01:57,787
I’m going to have this
medicine investigated.

917
01:02:00,549 --> 01:02:01,549
JoJo...

918
01:02:03,221 --> 01:02:05,414
If you doubt the validity
of that medicine,

919
01:02:05,442 --> 01:02:08,078
Then you doubt our very friendship.

920
01:02:08,993 --> 01:02:09,993
Dio,

921
01:02:10,745 --> 01:02:12,197
As a gentleman,

922
01:02:12,233 --> 01:02:15,470
I ask you to swear your innocence on
your father’s honour and the Brando name.

923
01:02:16,720 --> 01:02:18,711
If you can swear on your father’s honour,

924
01:02:19,062 --> 01:02:20,760
I’ll never speak of this again.

925
01:02:20,999 --> 01:02:23,001
Swear on that guy?

926
01:02:23,876 --> 01:02:24,876
Dio,

927
01:02:25,093 --> 01:02:25,849
Swear on it.

928
01:02:25,863 --> 01:02:27,607
DIO: Swear on it?
JOJO: Come on, swear on it!

929
01:02:27,628 --> 01:02:29,176
DIO: Swear...
JOJO: Swear on it now!

930
01:02:29,194 --> 01:02:30,583
DIO: Swear...
JOJO: Can you swear on it, Dio?!

931
01:02:30,608 --> 01:02:33,348
That scum has never had any
honour for me to swear on!

932
01:02:33,883 --> 01:02:35,592
Give me the medicine back!

933
01:02:43,227 --> 01:02:45,661
I won’t ever let you go
near my father again!

934
01:02:46,400 --> 01:02:47,596
I’m convinced now...

935
01:02:48,365 --> 01:02:50,768
That there was never any
friendship between us to begin with!

936
01:02:51,744 --> 01:02:54,085
I’ll protect the Joestar family.

937
01:02:54,124 --> 01:02:55,740
This is all a
misunderstanding, JoJo!

938
01:02:56,833 --> 01:02:58,127
Just a misunderstanding...

939
01:02:59,297 --> 01:03:00,397
Besides...

940
01:03:02,138 --> 01:03:03,599
It’s not like you have
any proof, do you?

941
01:03:04,877 --> 01:03:06,457
Nothing more than a flimsy theory.

942
01:03:07,885 --> 01:03:08,885
Yes,

943
01:03:09,193 --> 01:03:11,670
I despised my father, hated
him more than anything.

944
01:03:12,007 --> 01:03:14,886
I just lost my temper when
you started suspecting me...

945
01:03:15,240 --> 01:03:16,874
JoJo! JoJo!!

946
01:03:18,558 --> 01:03:19,558
JoJo...

947
01:03:21,107 --> 01:03:22,943
Is something the matter, Master Dio?

948
01:03:23,937 --> 01:03:24,937
No...

949
01:03:25,740 --> 01:03:27,041
I’m alright...

950
01:03:31,550 --> 01:03:36,031
<i>Dio Dio Dio Dio Dio!</i>

951
01:03:36,208 --> 01:03:38,674
It’s too late to turn back now.

952
01:03:39,755 --> 01:03:43,057
<i>A world where everything is perfect,</i>

953
01:03:43,578 --> 01:03:47,743
<i>In the palm of your hand, Dio!</i>

954
01:03:51,800 --> 01:03:53,268
Father!

955
01:03:53,290 --> 01:03:55,544
What’s going on, Young Master JoJo?!

956
01:03:54,525 --> 01:03:55,525
-Father!

957
01:03:55,565 --> 01:03:57,025
What’s all this ruckus for?

958
01:03:57,041 --> 01:03:58,058
Father...

959
01:03:58,100 --> 01:04:00,434
I’m going to London
for two or three days.

960
01:04:00,874 --> 01:04:05,327
While I’m gone, take only what the
doctors and nurses I’ve hired give you.

961
01:04:06,023 --> 01:04:09,569
Please don’t accept any care
or medicine from anyone else.

962
01:04:09,596 --> 01:04:10,773
Excuse me, but—

963
01:04:10,820 --> 01:04:13,414
We’ll do as he says.

964
01:04:14,270 --> 01:04:15,917
I don’t know what’s going on...

965
01:04:16,434 --> 01:04:19,579
But I trust my son!

966
01:04:20,050 --> 01:04:22,050
Thank you, Father.

967
01:04:28,442 --> 01:04:31,629
Seven years ago, this thing...

968
01:04:32,903 --> 01:04:35,715
It moved in reaction to my blood.

969
01:04:50,064 --> 01:04:51,475
With this...

970
01:04:54,554 --> 01:04:57,486
I’ll make it appear as if he had
an accident during his research.

971
01:05:01,399 --> 01:05:02,399
JoJo...

972
01:05:04,349 --> 01:05:06,402
Your own research...

973
01:05:07,025 --> 01:05:09,511
Will be the death of you!

974
01:05:34,346 --> 01:05:38,503
<i>Time’s nearly out, so I gathered
my resolve and took off!</i>

975
01:05:38,562 --> 01:05:41,812
<i>Turning my eyes to the stars
and praying for an antidote</i>

976
01:05:41,911 --> 01:05:46,014
<i>I headed for the fringe of
society, the East End of London</i>

977
01:05:46,089 --> 01:05:50,583
<i>Now I’ve arrived here
in this town steeped in mud</i>

978
01:05:50,654 --> 01:05:54,069
<i>Ogre Street, the place
where plagues are born</i>

979
01:05:54,553 --> 01:05:57,873
<i>Before my eyes lies
the underbelly of society</i>

980
01:05:57,939 --> 01:06:01,895
<i>But I have a reason why I must move forward</i>

981
01:06:01,978 --> 01:06:05,459
<i>Even if I were to lose
this right hand of mine</i>

982
01:06:05,540 --> 01:06:06,609
<i>I’ll look to the stars!</i>

983
01:06:06,628 --> 01:06:08,713
<i>At long last our meeting takes place</i>

984
01:06:08,738 --> 01:06:10,549
<i>There’s a scent in the air
and it smells like prey</i>

985
01:06:10,574 --> 01:06:12,859
<i>Sniffing you out through the
storm someone’s making his way</i>

986
01:06:12,883 --> 01:06:14,596
<i>It’s time for your
leader to take the stage</i>

987
01:06:14,647 --> 01:06:21,604
<i>(Ogre Street, we devour anything we can)</i>

988
01:06:22,759 --> 01:06:30,968
<i>(Ogre Street, here everything meets its end)</i>

989
01:06:32,771 --> 01:06:34,739
<i>Dunno what the hell
you came here for</i>

990
01:06:34,764 --> 01:06:36,845
<i>Bet you thought you
stood a good chance, huh?</i>

991
01:06:36,893 --> 01:06:38,879
<i>In a moment we’ll
devour all that hope</i>

992
01:06:38,902 --> 01:06:40,856
<i>This is Ogre Street and
we’re the ogres, duh!</i>

993
01:06:40,915 --> 01:06:45,019
<i>Got no problem with you bein’ naïve,
I’m just showin’ you the simple reality</i>

994
01:06:45,079 --> 01:06:46,944
<i>Hey hey hey,
how about it, rich boy?</i>

995
01:06:46,990 --> 01:06:48,946
<i>Want a taste of the
edge of this knife?</i>

996
01:06:49,011 --> 01:06:52,679
<i>We’re gonna strip you of all that you got
Put up a fight and your life will be lost</i>

997
01:06:52,752 --> 01:06:56,583
<i>This is Ogre Street!
Ain’t it obvious that we’d cheat?</i>

998
01:06:56,651 --> 01:06:58,549
<i>Us have-nots are gonna
steal your riches away!</i>

999
01:06:58,574 --> 01:07:01,027
<i>From your life to that foolish
heart—we’ll steal ‘em away!</i>

1000
01:07:01,147 --> 01:07:04,497
<i>Tail between your legs, you can
save your own skin by runnin’ away!</i>

1001
01:07:03,842 --> 01:07:05,342
{\an8}Is this guy insane?!

1002
01:07:05,237 --> 01:07:11,697
<i>(Ogre Street, go on and leave it all behind)</i>

1003
01:07:11,069 --> 01:07:14,069
{\an8}<i>I don’t care if I lose four fingers!</i>

1004
01:07:13,210 --> 01:07:19,143
<i>(Ogre Street, we’ll even fill
our stomachs with your life)</i>

1005
01:07:19,207 --> 01:07:23,127
<i>I came here for a reason!</i>

1006
01:07:23,551 --> 01:07:31,380
<i>You said you’re fine with
losing four fingers, hah?</i>

1007
01:07:31,495 --> 01:07:39,085
<i>(Ogre Street, why don’t we
put that resolve to the test?)</i>

1008
01:07:39,554 --> 01:07:43,541
Hold on! I only came here
looking for a poison seller!

1009
01:07:43,611 --> 01:07:47,486
Quit bluffin’! Let me have a
go at this soft little rich boy!

1010
01:08:04,822 --> 01:08:07,118
That’s the sound of blade hitting bone!

1011
01:08:08,075 --> 01:08:11,454
<i>Made the mistake of my life, pickin’
a fight with this fearless tough guy</i>

1012
01:08:11,487 --> 01:08:13,684
<i>Countdown to my final breath—</i>

1013
01:08:13,732 --> 01:08:15,732
<i>Three, two, one!</i>

1014
01:08:27,940 --> 01:08:29,119
Stop, everyone!

1015
01:08:30,878 --> 01:08:34,911
I, Speedwagon, won’t allow you
to lay a hand on that gentleman!

1016
01:08:35,316 --> 01:08:37,133
Why didn’t you kick me
with your full strength?

1017
01:08:37,692 --> 01:08:39,354
I came here for the sake of my father.

1018
01:08:39,895 --> 01:08:41,415
So in the moment I kicked,

1019
01:08:41,463 --> 01:08:44,075
I thought you must have a father,
or mother, or siblings too.

1020
01:08:45,358 --> 01:08:47,694
I didn’t want to do anything
to cause your father grief.

1021
01:08:50,734 --> 01:08:52,644
Tell me your name!

1022
01:08:54,439 --> 01:08:55,880
Jonathan Joestar.

1023
01:08:56,320 --> 01:08:59,708
Mr. Joestar, if you’re looking
for poison, that’d be Wang Chan.

1024
01:08:59,921 --> 01:09:02,238
Be careful, he’s a crafty one!

1025
01:09:02,991 --> 01:09:04,233
Someone bandage his wound.

1026
01:09:04,317 --> 01:09:06,555
I, Speedwagon, will lead you to his shop!

1027
01:09:06,617 --> 01:09:07,355
Why?!

1028
01:09:07,400 --> 01:09:10,256
‘Cause I’ve taken a liking to ya!

1029
01:09:12,580 --> 01:09:16,336
<i>(Ogre Street)</i>

1030
01:09:16,692 --> 01:09:20,552
<i>With your determination to fight</i>

1031
01:09:20,701 --> 01:09:28,724
<i>(Ogre Street, you’ve lit in
us a glowing guiding light)</i>

1032
01:09:28,794 --> 01:09:32,834
<i>(You, who have the courage)</i>

1033
01:09:32,912 --> 01:09:36,881
<i>(To see the stars down here in the mud)</i>

1034
01:09:36,976 --> 01:09:44,954
<i>(Light up the darkness with
your unwavering heart!)</i>

1035
01:09:45,739 --> 01:09:47,169
<i>Your refreshing sunlight</i>

1036
01:09:47,547 --> 01:09:49,215
<i>Brought me completely to my knees</i>

1037
01:09:49,320 --> 01:09:50,843
<i>This must be some
strange twist of fate!</i>

1038
01:09:50,885 --> 01:09:52,313
<i>Let’s toast—to our meeting!</i>

1039
01:10:13,943 --> 01:10:14,943
JoJo...

1040
01:10:20,107 --> 01:10:21,107
JoJo...!

1041
01:10:32,824 --> 01:10:36,074
<i>Dio...</i>

1042
01:10:37,029 --> 01:10:39,061
JoJo has gone off to London...

1043
01:10:39,372 --> 01:10:41,274
Could he have died a dog’s death already?

1044
01:10:41,849 --> 01:10:45,357
<i>Dio...</i>

1045
01:10:45,907 --> 01:10:48,257
Or could he have found
evidence of the medicine?

1046
01:10:48,594 --> 01:10:49,594
Which is it?!

1047
01:10:50,408 --> 01:10:54,089
<i>Dio...</i>

1048
01:10:54,741 --> 01:10:57,898
Booze! I can’t help but drink!

1049
01:10:59,193 --> 01:11:03,535
<i>Can’t you hear my voice?</i>

1050
01:11:03,577 --> 01:11:06,413
<i>The voice calling for you?</i>

1051
01:11:06,058 --> 01:11:08,169
-Shut up, get out of my head!

1052
01:11:08,208 --> 01:11:12,656
<i>You’re the only one I care about</i>

1053
01:11:12,730 --> 01:11:16,930
<i>Become the richest man!</i>

1054
01:11:15,163 --> 01:11:17,351
-You piece of shit, we’re not the same!

1055
01:11:17,844 --> 01:11:20,337
Watch where you’re going, twat!

1056
01:11:21,270 --> 01:11:24,216
Oi, are you listening, you stupid brat?

1057
01:11:24,252 --> 01:11:27,440
You should ask yer mum to hold
you by the hand next time!

1058
01:11:25,771 --> 01:11:30,041
{\an8}<i>Can’t you hear my voice?</i>

1059
01:11:27,687 --> 01:11:29,833
Didn’t you hear me?

1060
01:11:30,086 --> 01:11:32,778
Oi! You piece of shit—

1061
01:11:30,364 --> 01:11:33,896
{\an8}<i>Are you stupid? Oi, Dio!</i>

1062
01:11:34,912 --> 01:11:39,150
{\an8}<i>Can’t you hear my voice?</i>

1063
01:11:34,915 --> 01:11:39,568
You filthy old tramps with
no sense of personal hygiene...

1064
01:11:39,200 --> 01:11:43,438
{\an8}<i>Are you stupid? Oi, Dio!</i>

1065
01:11:40,677 --> 01:11:42,602
How dare you! You bastard!

1066
01:11:42,829 --> 01:11:44,763
What did you do to my mate?!

1067
01:11:45,056 --> 01:11:49,183
{\an8}<i>One man’s misfortune...</i>

1068
01:11:46,583 --> 01:11:48,006
I’ll kill you!

1069
01:11:49,422 --> 01:11:51,974
{\an8}<i>Is another man’s fortune!</i>

1070
01:11:51,222 --> 01:11:54,001
Interesting, this is a good
opportunity to try it out!

1071
01:11:52,829 --> 01:11:55,481
{\an8}<i>You’re my clever boy!</i>

1072
01:11:54,028 --> 01:11:55,671
What’re you mumbling about?!

1073
01:11:57,299 --> 01:11:59,813
It’s a live human experiment!

1074
01:12:01,038 --> 01:12:06,245
{\an8}<i>Dio Dio Dio Dio Dio!</i>

1075
01:12:04,884 --> 01:12:06,514
JoJo!

1076
01:12:07,023 --> 01:12:10,508
I’ll find the answer to your
research myself right now!

1077
01:12:09,947 --> 01:12:14,362
{\an8}<i>Dio Dio Dio Dio Dio!</i>

1078
01:12:16,450 --> 01:12:17,450
What...

1079
01:12:19,242 --> 01:12:20,242
What—

1080
01:12:20,720 --> 01:12:25,934
{\an8}<i>[AZTEC CHANTING]</i>

1081
01:12:21,852 --> 01:12:24,051
What is this light?

1082
01:12:27,453 --> 01:12:28,759
Was I hallucinating?

1083
01:12:30,857 --> 01:12:32,157
He’s dead...

1084
01:12:32,519 --> 01:12:35,640
The spikes pierced so deep into his skull,
it must have killed him instantly.

1085
01:12:35,738 --> 01:12:39,094
This mask is just some ancient
sacrificial torture device.

1086
01:12:39,777 --> 01:12:41,235
He’s not dead!

1087
01:12:43,652 --> 01:12:46,124
Fangs?! What is he?!

1088
01:13:07,518 --> 01:13:12,056
<i>I’m thirsty, thirsty, so thirsty!</i>

1089
01:13:12,157 --> 01:13:14,343
He’s sucking my blood!

1090
01:13:16,667 --> 01:13:17,830
His face is...

1091
01:13:18,190 --> 01:13:19,468
Becoming younger?!

1092
01:13:22,400 --> 01:13:27,296
I don’t want the morning sun
to be the last thing I ever see!

1093
01:13:43,462 --> 01:13:45,063
I was saved...

1094
01:13:52,766 --> 01:13:54,288
By the sunlight...

1095
01:13:56,843 --> 01:13:58,329
He turned into ash...

1096
01:14:03,817 --> 01:14:04,539
Ow!

1097
01:14:09,472 --> 01:14:10,572
So this...

1098
01:14:14,262 --> 01:14:16,453
Is the power of the Stone Mask.

1099
01:14:21,697 --> 01:14:23,258
So, where is Dio?

1100
01:14:23,277 --> 01:14:24,960
It seems he hasn’t come
home since last night.

1101
01:14:24,977 --> 01:14:26,326
I’ll call for reinforcements right away.

1102
01:14:26,341 --> 01:14:27,418
Please use the foyer.

1103
01:14:27,453 --> 01:14:28,357
Thank you.

1104
01:14:28,587 --> 01:14:29,567
-You there!
-Sir!

1105
01:14:29,603 --> 01:14:31,995
This Asian fellow,
Wang Chan—take him away.

1106
01:14:32,075 --> 01:14:32,862
Yes sir!

1107
01:14:36,368 --> 01:14:38,243
Oi, come on!

1108
01:14:39,468 --> 01:14:40,468
JoJo...

1109
01:14:41,026 --> 01:14:42,280
I apologise.

1110
01:14:42,610 --> 01:14:44,427
This is my cross to bear.

1111
01:14:45,172 --> 01:14:46,077
What?

1112
01:14:46,103 --> 01:14:49,548
If only I had made sure
that man was exiled...

1113
01:14:50,084 --> 01:14:51,174
Dio’s father...

1114
01:14:51,751 --> 01:14:53,219
Dario Brando.

1115
01:14:54,101 --> 01:14:55,648
What do you mean?

1116
01:14:56,924 --> 01:14:59,417
I’ll tell you about it.

1117
01:15:00,228 --> 01:15:03,597
This happened when you were a baby.

1118
01:15:05,103 --> 01:15:08,793
This is certainly my ring,

1119
01:15:09,080 --> 01:15:11,887
But I never reported a theft.

1120
01:15:11,932 --> 01:15:15,209
I arrested the man who
was caught pawning it.

1121
01:15:15,684 --> 01:15:22,064
Lord Joestar had that ring specially made
as a pair for his and his wife’s engagement.

1122
01:15:22,111 --> 01:15:23,988
It was obvious that it was stolen!

1123
01:15:24,382 --> 01:15:29,410
Yes, it’s the ring I had made with my wife.

1124
01:15:31,059 --> 01:15:34,683
When Lord Joestar thought about his wife,

1125
01:15:35,272 --> 01:15:37,156
Tears welled up in his eyes.

1126
01:15:37,761 --> 01:15:38,761
I...

1127
01:15:39,314 --> 01:15:40,828
I arrested the criminal!

1128
01:15:40,869 --> 01:15:42,293
Would you like to see for yourself?

1129
01:15:42,339 --> 01:15:44,657
Stealing from a noble is a heavy offence.

1130
01:15:44,683 --> 01:15:46,932
He’s certain to be exiled!

1131
01:15:47,721 --> 01:15:48,721
I see.

1132
01:15:49,438 --> 01:15:54,219
Here he is! Oi! Wake up! Brando!

1133
01:15:55,401 --> 01:15:56,398
Brando?!

1134
01:15:56,411 --> 01:15:57,682
Oh, bollocks.

1135
01:15:57,739 --> 01:15:58,295
Then that means—

1136
01:15:58,342 --> 01:16:01,386
Dario Brando isn’t some saviour,

1137
01:16:01,444 --> 01:16:02,809
But a thief!

1138
01:16:03,382 --> 01:16:08,495
Even knowing this,
Lord Joestar adopted Dio.

1139
01:16:10,464 --> 01:16:11,464
Why?

1140
01:16:11,692 --> 01:16:12,692
I...

1141
01:16:13,308 --> 01:16:15,869
I was moved to tears by
what Lord Joestar said next.

1142
01:16:20,058 --> 01:16:24,230
Did he tell you...

1143
01:16:25,186 --> 01:16:28,443
That I gave him this ring?

1144
01:16:28,526 --> 01:16:30,518
Yes, he said that. A lie!

1145
01:16:30,536 --> 01:16:31,675
It’s not a lie.

1146
01:16:32,445 --> 01:16:35,577
This is what I gave him.

1147
01:16:36,184 --> 01:16:37,736
He is innocent.

1148
01:16:37,756 --> 01:16:39,759
But it’s a memento of your wife!

1149
01:16:39,783 --> 01:16:40,783
Mr. Brando,

1150
01:16:41,601 --> 01:16:43,110
This is yours.

1151
01:16:43,692 --> 01:16:48,499
With this ring, please buy
what you need for your family.

1152
01:16:48,542 --> 01:16:51,204
Lord Joestar! Are you taking the piss?!

1153
01:16:58,239 --> 01:17:08,782
<i>If I were suffering from poverty</i>

1154
01:17:10,394 --> 01:17:20,799
<i>I would have done the same
thing, yes, for the ones I love</i>

1155
01:17:22,609 --> 01:17:33,345
<i>When the stars in the sky
shine, they start to tell a story</i>

1156
01:17:34,737 --> 01:17:47,249
<i>Let’s pray that this light
will illuminate the darkness</i>

1157
01:17:47,466 --> 01:17:49,336
Thank you, sir!

1158
01:17:50,057 --> 01:17:53,546
You are too good-natured!

1159
01:17:53,588 --> 01:17:57,449
This scumbag will laugh at
you tomorrow morning!

1160
01:17:59,288 --> 01:18:00,882
That may be true,

1161
01:18:01,493 --> 01:18:04,342
But think about it the other way around.

1162
01:18:05,044 --> 01:18:15,227
<i>From the prison called fate,
people reach for the stars</i>

1163
01:18:16,989 --> 01:18:25,348
<i>Let’s embrace that courage,
that loneliness,</i>

1164
01:18:25,892 --> 01:18:29,896
<i>That pain</i>

1165
01:18:30,994 --> 01:18:36,749
<i>Everything is connected</i>

1166
01:18:36,818 --> 01:18:42,929
<i>There’s a meaning to it all</i>

1167
01:18:43,275 --> 01:18:53,023
<i>I believe in humanity
and all of its resolve</i>

1168
01:18:53,174 --> 01:18:55,523
I can’t see stars or nothin’!
That’s bollocks!

1169
01:18:55,624 --> 01:18:56,862
That’s why...

1170
01:18:58,530 --> 01:19:04,011
<i>I’ll keep on believing</i>

1171
01:19:04,297 --> 01:19:10,154
<i>That this gold I’ve passed on</i>

1172
01:19:10,564 --> 01:19:16,131
<i>Will shine one day</i>

1173
01:19:16,290 --> 01:19:20,762
<i>With all of my resolve...</i>

1174
01:19:23,258 --> 01:19:37,110
<i>I will defy fate!</i>

1175
01:19:41,292 --> 01:19:42,292
Inspector.

1176
01:19:43,916 --> 01:19:45,360
I’ll wait for Dio.

1177
01:19:47,461 --> 01:19:49,062
He can still be stopped.

1178
01:20:12,444 --> 01:20:15,259
I heard a bizarre rumour on the streets.

1179
01:20:15,982 --> 01:20:20,000
It’s said that a vagabond shattered
a wall with his bare hands.

1180
01:20:20,515 --> 01:20:22,640
And then...

1181
01:20:23,244 --> 01:20:27,156
When the morning sun hit the man,
he turned to ashes and vanished.

1182
01:20:29,774 --> 01:20:35,752
It’s the same as what
happened 30 years ago...

1183
01:20:36,915 --> 01:20:45,293
<i>It’s a wedge driven into
the wasteland of my memory</i>

1184
01:20:46,273 --> 01:20:55,378
<i>At dawn, a blood-red sun
rose over the Atlantic Ocean</i>

1185
01:20:56,327 --> 01:21:05,303
<i>Full of passion and yearning
for the unknown world</i>

1186
01:21:05,515 --> 01:21:14,417
<i>I crossed the seven seas
with my respected father</i>

1187
01:21:14,588 --> 01:21:23,228
<i>My beloved father, the voices
of my friends, my youth</i>

1188
01:21:24,346 --> 01:21:33,049
<i>The Stone Mask took
everything away from me</i>

1189
01:21:33,502 --> 01:21:38,255
<i>I swore I’d get revenge,
that I’d take it all back</i>

1190
01:21:38,335 --> 01:21:42,426
<i>Maybe not today, but
there’s always tomorrow</i>

1191
01:21:42,471 --> 01:21:45,875
<i>Yes, tomorrow...</i>

1192
01:21:49,761 --> 01:21:52,507
“A man is what he thinks
about all day long.”

1193
01:21:52,542 --> 01:21:55,931
There’s a saying that goes like that.

1194
01:21:58,564 --> 01:21:59,960
The Stone Mask...

1195
01:22:01,295 --> 01:22:04,472
If I don’t find it, I can’t
recover what I’ve lost.

1196
01:22:18,104 --> 01:22:19,625
I, Dio, was...

1197
01:22:23,718 --> 01:22:24,718
Shit...

1198
01:22:28,727 --> 01:22:29,727
JoJo...

1199
01:22:33,416 --> 01:22:35,781
I see you’ve returned from London—

1200
01:22:35,804 --> 01:22:37,425
I have the antidote now.

1201
01:22:43,826 --> 01:22:45,562
It’s a shame it had
to come to this, Dio.

1202
01:22:46,521 --> 01:22:47,836
It truly hurts me.

1203
01:22:50,591 --> 01:22:52,662
Although you might not believe me,

1204
01:22:54,127 --> 01:22:55,628
Those are my true feelings.

1205
01:23:01,673 --> 01:23:03,207
I understand, JoJo.

1206
01:23:05,505 --> 01:23:07,451
You’re honest like that.

1207
01:23:11,503 --> 01:23:13,361
Although it’s selfish,
I have a favour to ask—

1208
01:23:15,401 --> 01:23:16,815
The final one
I will ask of you.

1209
01:23:18,085 --> 01:23:19,919
Can you give me more time?

1210
01:23:21,318 --> 01:23:22,318
Time—

1211
01:23:24,286 --> 01:23:25,813
To turn myself in to the police.

1212
01:23:27,275 --> 01:23:28,275
Eh?

1213
01:23:30,203 --> 01:23:31,203
I...

1214
01:23:33,420 --> 01:23:36,699
R-Regret the choices I’ve
made throughout my life.

1215
01:23:40,704 --> 01:23:42,739
Because I was born into squalor...

1216
01:23:46,150 --> 01:23:48,356
My ambition was relentless.

1217
01:23:52,411 --> 01:23:54,180
What I did was terrible!

1218
01:23:57,261 --> 01:23:59,315
I want to repent for my sins!

1219
01:23:59,900 --> 01:24:02,847
Don’t believe a word he says!

1220
01:24:12,231 --> 01:24:14,974
I can see from your face that
you’re wondering who I am.

1221
01:24:15,027 --> 01:24:17,010
Allow me to introduce myself!

1222
01:24:17,564 --> 01:24:20,065
I’m Speedwagon, the meddler!

1223
01:24:20,818 --> 01:24:23,808
Growing up in the darkest slums,

1224
01:24:24,105 --> 01:24:26,352
I’ve met all sorts of horrible
people throughout my life.

1225
01:24:26,884 --> 01:24:29,650
So I can tell all I need to know
about a person just from their smell.

1226
01:24:33,796 --> 01:24:35,423
This guy reeks!

1227
01:24:35,449 --> 01:24:38,390
Worse than vomit!

1228
01:24:38,620 --> 01:24:40,486
He was born evil!

1229
01:24:40,537 --> 01:24:43,224
Mr. Joestar, you should call
for the police right away.

1230
01:24:45,737 --> 01:24:47,795
This man has confessed already.

1231
01:24:50,445 --> 01:24:51,270
Father...

1232
01:24:51,290 --> 01:24:53,784
I’ve heard everything I need to.

1233
01:24:58,615 --> 01:25:01,243
I will return to my bed to rest.

1234
01:25:03,802 --> 01:25:09,563
I don’t want to see my son
being taken away in handcuffs.

1235
01:25:10,858 --> 01:25:13,615
You won’t succeed in arresting that man...

1236
01:25:14,361 --> 01:25:17,034
He was born with an innate destiny.

1237
01:25:17,079 --> 01:25:18,079
Silence!

1238
01:25:18,397 --> 01:25:19,397
Come on—

1239
01:25:22,171 --> 01:25:23,729
JoJo, I understand!

1240
01:25:25,181 --> 01:25:26,579
Arrest me.

1241
01:25:27,637 --> 01:25:29,065
But, if it’s not too much to ask;

1242
01:25:29,309 --> 01:25:31,128
I want you to be the
one who handcuffs me.

1243
01:25:32,038 --> 01:25:34,130
For the sake of those seven
years we spent together.

1244
01:25:34,377 --> 01:25:35,377
Be careful!

1245
01:25:36,841 --> 01:25:37,841
Agreed.

1246
01:25:38,848 --> 01:25:40,337
I will handcuff you.

1247
01:25:47,389 --> 01:25:52,992
<i>To be human is to have limits</i>

1248
01:25:53,079 --> 01:25:58,645
<i>That’s what I’ve come to realise</i>

1249
01:25:59,650 --> 01:26:03,837
<i>And still the more I try to plan,</i>

1250
01:26:04,992 --> 01:26:09,015
<i>The more I see the limitations of this life</i>

1251
01:26:09,044 --> 01:26:10,044
What’re you talking about?

1252
01:26:10,080 --> 01:26:11,080
<i>You know, JoJo...</i>

1253
01:26:11,642 --> 01:26:14,924
<i>This frustration, it’s unbearable</i>

1254
01:26:15,699 --> 01:26:22,511
<i>I’m always coming up empty-handed</i>

1255
01:26:24,111 --> 01:26:33,017
<i>This prison I’m trapped in,
it’s slathered in mud</i>

1256
01:26:34,473 --> 01:26:39,285
<i>I can’t see the stars, and no
matter how hard I struggle,</i>

1257
01:26:39,886 --> 01:26:43,658
<i>My eyes are still blinded</i>

1258
01:26:44,929 --> 01:26:47,160
<i>Don’t you get it?</i>

1259
01:26:47,187 --> 01:26:49,527
<i>That murky sky up there,</i>

1260
01:26:50,069 --> 01:26:54,711
<i>It’s crushing me!
I can’t reach up this way</i>

1261
01:26:55,030 --> 01:26:59,518
<i>Yes, Joestar, even
your purest pedigree,</i>

1262
01:26:59,869 --> 01:27:04,047
<i>Can’t wash the filth out of mine</i>

1263
01:27:04,308 --> 01:27:06,382
<i>That’s why, now is the time</i>

1264
01:27:06,431 --> 01:27:08,661
<i>To break free, from this cage</i>

1265
01:27:08,687 --> 01:27:10,960
<i>And seize...</i>

1266
01:27:11,388 --> 01:27:14,419
<i>The stars!</i>

1267
01:27:16,804 --> 01:27:17,804
The Stone Mask?

1268
01:27:20,646 --> 01:27:22,214
<i>I...</i>

1269
01:27:25,884 --> 01:27:26,884
<i>I...</i>

1270
01:27:29,282 --> 01:27:32,330
<i>Reject...</i>

1271
01:27:33,308 --> 01:27:37,730
<i>My humanity!</i>

1272
01:27:38,512 --> 01:27:42,629
<i>JoJo!</i>

1273
01:27:42,685 --> 01:27:43,948
Stop!

1274
01:27:46,579 --> 01:27:47,725
-JoJo!
-Father!

1275
01:27:47,927 --> 01:27:48,927
Dio!

1276
01:27:49,498 --> 01:27:50,451
Dio!

1277
01:27:55,179 --> 01:27:58,245
Shoot him!

1278
01:27:58,546 --> 01:28:01,236
Shoot him!

1279
01:28:03,477 --> 01:28:04,571
Lord Joestar!

1280
01:28:04,590 --> 01:28:06,856
Hey—a doctor! Call a doctor!

1281
01:28:06,879 --> 01:28:08,488
Father! Father!

1282
01:28:11,307 --> 01:28:12,307
JoJo...

1283
01:28:15,543 --> 01:28:16,543
This is...

1284
01:28:20,858 --> 01:28:23,572
Your late mother’s ring.

1285
01:28:23,601 --> 01:28:25,827
A doctor’s coming, he’ll save you! Hold on!

1286
01:28:29,425 --> 01:28:33,633
Please... don’t blame Dio for this.

1287
01:28:36,894 --> 01:28:40,768
Maybe... the fact that
I was so hard on you...

1288
01:28:42,700 --> 01:28:46,844
Made him feel like I was
treating him differently.

1289
01:28:48,035 --> 01:28:49,035
Father...

1290
01:28:56,448 --> 01:28:58,547
It’s not so bad...

1291
01:29:00,823 --> 01:29:01,823
JoJo...

1292
01:29:07,174 --> 01:29:08,529
To die...

1293
01:29:11,941 --> 01:29:16,780
In my son’s arms.

1294
01:29:31,903 --> 01:29:32,903
Father?

1295
01:29:35,727 --> 01:29:37,376
How could this be...

1296
01:29:38,662 --> 01:29:42,270
I knew I made a mistake, back then.

1297
01:29:43,072 --> 01:29:45,577
Now he’s dead and there’s
no bringing him back.

1298
01:29:46,600 --> 01:29:47,844
Mr. Joestar...

1299
01:29:49,652 --> 01:29:55,220
<i>You always told me to be a gentleman</i>

1300
01:29:56,877 --> 01:30:01,530
<i>To always live with pride</i>

1301
01:30:04,353 --> 01:30:10,005
<i>Even though I said I’d save you,</i>

1302
01:30:11,890 --> 01:30:17,397
<i>Even though you said you believed me!</i>

1303
01:30:19,387 --> 01:30:24,890
<i>I couldn’t protect you—
How could I be so powerless?</i>

1304
01:30:26,829 --> 01:30:29,597
<i>What does it mean
to be a gentleman?</i>

1305
01:30:29,638 --> 01:30:33,835
<i>Father, open your eyes!</i>

1306
01:30:33,952 --> 01:30:36,956
<i>What’s pride worth now?</i>

1307
01:30:37,012 --> 01:30:39,583
<i>What’s the purpose of</i>

1308
01:30:41,083 --> 01:30:48,365
<i>This Joestar blood
flowing through my body?</i>

1309
01:30:49,365 --> 01:30:54,964
<i>You always remained a
gentleman, until the very end</i>

1310
01:30:56,662 --> 01:31:03,321
<i>Carrying yourself with
discipline and pride</i>

1311
01:31:04,115 --> 01:31:11,359
<i>Your resolve to shine a beacon
through the dark wastelands</i>

1312
01:31:11,785 --> 01:31:17,108
<i>I’ll accept it all, and
look up at the stars</i>

1313
01:31:19,240 --> 01:31:24,735
<i>I’ll engrave your will into my soul</i>

1314
01:31:26,538 --> 01:31:33,838
<i>Take pride in this heart
that shines like gold!</i>

1315
01:31:34,183 --> 01:31:39,298
<i>It will become the future,
sent up to the stars</i>

1316
01:31:40,727 --> 01:31:48,284
<i>This Joestar blood
flowing through my body!</i>

1317
01:31:48,462 --> 01:31:53,831
<i>Everything is connected,
there’s a meaning to it all</i>

1318
01:31:55,913 --> 01:32:01,238
<i>I’ll fight against this fate,
keep sorrow at bay</i>

1319
01:32:01,699 --> 01:32:08,003
<i>With just one drop of courage!</i>

1320
01:32:18,955 --> 01:32:20,756
Inspector! It’s an emergency!

1321
01:32:20,795 --> 01:32:21,658
What’s wrong?

1322
01:32:21,682 --> 01:32:24,808
The body... Dio’s body is gone!

1323
01:32:24,847 --> 01:32:25,934
What?!

1324
01:32:26,244 --> 01:32:27,343
What did you say?!

1325
01:32:29,238 --> 01:32:31,434
Oi copper, get away from the window!

1326
01:32:32,758 --> 01:32:34,551
Inspector!

1327
01:32:42,561 --> 01:32:45,085
What the hell?! He came back to life!

1328
01:32:45,113 --> 01:32:47,168
Even though we shot him into Swiss cheese!

1329
01:32:47,204 --> 01:32:49,799
Be careful! He’s got some kind of weapon!

1330
01:32:50,768 --> 01:32:51,768
Dio!

1331
01:32:52,106 --> 01:32:53,106
Stop!

1332
01:32:55,363 --> 01:32:58,360
Shoot him! Don’t just
stand there! Quickly!

1333
01:33:06,724 --> 01:33:10,126
I don’t get it! I can’t make heads
or tails of what’s happening!

1334
01:33:11,483 --> 01:33:13,203
JoJo!

1335
01:33:14,163 --> 01:33:18,693
Can you hear my voice?

1336
01:33:19,373 --> 01:33:20,903
H-He’s sucking his blood!

1337
01:33:33,500 --> 01:33:34,666
You’re—

1338
01:33:34,688 --> 01:33:37,470
JoJo...

1339
01:33:37,527 --> 01:33:44,434
I’ve gained such incredible power!

1340
01:33:45,672 --> 01:33:48,004
From the Stone Mask...

1341
01:33:49,705 --> 01:33:54,104
From your father’s blood!

1342
01:33:54,217 --> 01:33:55,217
Dio!

1343
01:33:55,297 --> 01:33:57,741
These monsters are
making <i>more</i> monsters?!

1344
01:33:57,793 --> 01:34:00,180
Run away, Mr. Joestar!
You’ll only get killed!

1345
01:34:00,206 --> 01:34:02,238
That monster is too bloody strong!

1346
01:34:07,857 --> 01:34:08,704
The brain!

1347
01:34:09,124 --> 01:34:12,604
That mask must have drawn out
an unknown power from his brain!

1348
01:34:13,372 --> 01:34:14,528
If that’s the case...

1349
01:34:15,997 --> 01:34:18,584
I’ll have to completely destroy his head!

1350
01:34:28,421 --> 01:34:29,030
Stop!

1351
01:34:29,064 --> 01:34:30,064
Speedwagon!

1352
01:34:38,342 --> 01:34:39,654
I must...

1353
01:34:41,255 --> 01:34:43,801
I must make my will stronger!

1354
01:34:58,952 --> 01:35:00,847
JoJo!

1355
01:35:04,082 --> 01:35:07,656
Weak! So weak!

1356
01:35:11,704 --> 01:35:12,918
Mr. Joestar!

1357
01:35:12,931 --> 01:35:13,986
Let me...

1358
01:35:14,022 --> 01:35:19,157
Let me enjoy this amazing power
for just a little longer!

1359
01:35:19,628 --> 01:35:25,073
After all, I still don’t know
what I’m capable of yet!

1360
01:35:33,175 --> 01:35:36,180
JoJo...

1361
01:35:37,212 --> 01:35:41,384
Stop this useless struggle of yours.

1362
01:35:42,928 --> 01:35:44,484
I told you, didn’t I?

1363
01:35:45,447 --> 01:35:48,067
No matter how many
tricks you come up with,

1364
01:35:48,815 --> 01:35:52,397
Humans have limits!

1365
01:35:54,885 --> 01:35:59,999
Quit hiding behind that
curtain! Come out here!

1366
01:36:01,257 --> 01:36:06,411
You and your friend
can become my lifeforce!

1367
01:36:10,863 --> 01:36:11,823
Dio!

1368
01:36:11,881 --> 01:36:13,826
This isn’t a “trick” I’m using to stop you!

1369
01:36:14,474 --> 01:36:15,521
It’s courage!

1370
01:36:18,005 --> 01:36:19,563
This fire won’t kill him.

1371
01:36:20,273 --> 01:36:22,832
Speedwagon, escape from the mansion.

1372
01:36:22,880 --> 01:36:23,880
What?

1373
01:36:24,460 --> 01:36:25,500
Mr. Joestar!

1374
01:36:26,540 --> 01:36:28,762
Don’t run upstairs!

1375
01:36:39,812 --> 01:36:45,135
<i>(The flash of flames,
illuminating the dark)</i>

1376
01:36:45,915 --> 01:36:48,484
<i>Come, Dio.</i>

1377
01:36:48,934 --> 01:36:51,958
<i>I’m up here.</i>

1378
01:36:52,350 --> 01:36:54,945
<i>Is that an invitation, JoJo?</i>

1379
01:36:54,981 --> 01:36:58,570
<i>Very well, I’ll take care of you first</i>

1380
01:36:58,658 --> 01:37:03,927
<i>(The flash of flames,
scattering the light)</i>

1381
01:37:04,914 --> 01:37:10,366
<i>I’ll put an end to you and
your cursed powers here!</i>

1382
01:37:10,434 --> 01:37:12,595
<i>It’s useless! Useless! Useless!</i>

1383
01:37:12,676 --> 01:37:17,397
<i>I’ll suck you dry!</i>

1384
01:37:17,465 --> 01:37:20,211
<i>(The flames are pulsing)</i>

1385
01:37:20,639 --> 01:37:26,793
<i>JOJO: Father! I’ll mourn you
DIO: I offer you my thanks</i>

1386
01:37:22,695 --> 01:37:26,517
{\an8}<i>(Flickering from light to dark)</i>

1387
01:37:26,856 --> 01:37:31,582
<i>JOJO: Please give me strength
DIO: For giving me strength</i>

1388
01:37:31,635 --> 01:37:36,021
<i>I always walked in your shadow</i>

1389
01:37:36,071 --> 01:37:40,144
<i>You were always right behind me</i>

1390
01:37:40,190 --> 01:37:43,902
<i>My youth was with you</i>

1391
01:37:44,385 --> 01:37:48,706
<i>It’s time for us to say goodbye to it</i>

1392
01:37:48,761 --> 01:37:49,761
JoJo!

1393
01:37:49,902 --> 01:37:53,269
<i>The Joestar manor is burning</i>

1394
01:37:53,324 --> 01:37:55,324
<i>And Father is dead!</i>

1395
01:37:56,211 --> 01:38:01,846
<i>I’ve lost everything, save for my life</i>

1396
01:38:02,492 --> 01:38:08,476
<i>I’ll let that burn to ash too.
I’ll stop you, Dio!</i>

1397
01:38:18,894 --> 01:38:22,013
Mr. Joestar was surely thinking,

1398
01:38:22,065 --> 01:38:27,722
That a stronger fire could overpower
that demon’s healing ability.

1399
01:38:27,779 --> 01:38:31,916
“If only the flames were
even hotter!” But by then...

1400
01:38:31,957 --> 01:38:34,848
The fire had already engulfed the
mansion, even overtaking the roof.

1401
01:38:34,903 --> 01:38:39,375
Damn it! Mr. Joestar!

1402
01:39:11,872 --> 01:39:14,501
This body is immortal.

1403
01:39:15,311 --> 01:39:18,922
The only one dying will be you!

1404
01:39:20,131 --> 01:39:24,472
<i>(The goddess of familial love
is flickering in flames)</i>

1405
01:39:24,519 --> 01:39:28,259
<i>(Equally doling out love and judgement)</i>

1406
01:39:28,527 --> 01:39:32,449
<i>(The goddess of familial love
is flickering in flames)</i>

1407
01:39:32,521 --> 01:39:36,855
<i>(Equally doling out love and judgement)</i>

1408
01:39:35,286 --> 01:39:36,786
-JoJo!

1409
01:39:36,951 --> 01:39:41,056
<i>I won’t let go of this knife,</i>

1410
01:39:41,095 --> 01:39:43,474
The knife you stabbed Father with!

1411
01:39:43,500 --> 01:39:45,516
It’s useless! I’m immortal!

1412
01:39:45,575 --> 01:39:53,486
<i>With this final bit of strength</i>

1413
01:39:46,492 --> 01:39:49,651
{\an8}<i>(The goddess of familial love
is flickering in flames)</i>

1414
01:39:49,707 --> 01:39:53,413
{\an8}<i>(Equally doling out love and judgement)</i>

1415
01:39:53,617 --> 01:39:57,800
<i>(The goddess of familial love
is flickering in flames)</i>

1416
01:39:57,850 --> 01:40:02,408
<i>(Equally doling out love and judgement)</i>

1417
01:40:02,471 --> 01:40:07,534
<i>This can’t be how my life ends—</i>

1418
01:40:07,625 --> 01:40:12,480
JoJo!!

1419
01:41:13,105 --> 01:41:14,452
Can you hear me?

1420
01:41:17,279 --> 01:41:18,579
You can hear me.

1421
01:41:20,874 --> 01:41:21,874
Good.

1422
01:41:23,111 --> 01:41:25,467
I hope you had a nice intermission.

1423
01:41:30,794 --> 01:41:34,656
I’ve returned in order to
continue telling our story,

1424
01:41:35,259 --> 01:41:39,799
Of the world to which all of
you have become witnesses.

1425
01:41:40,666 --> 01:41:44,211
And so that we can continue our
<i>show</i> of love for these characters.

1426
01:41:45,205 --> 01:41:47,811
I want the whole acrylic stand collection.

1427
01:41:53,950 --> 01:41:56,519
Just a few more until it’s complete!

1428
01:41:57,772 --> 01:42:03,153
I hope you get the merch
you’re looking for too.

1429
01:42:08,018 --> 01:42:12,407
Well, let’s continue where we left off.

1430
01:42:13,576 --> 01:42:18,311
The story up to this point
seems like a bit of a fairytale, but...

1431
01:42:18,580 --> 01:42:20,958
Make no mistake, it’s the truth.

1432
01:42:21,515 --> 01:42:26,425
Things are going to get more
and more bizarre from here on out.

1433
01:42:26,950 --> 01:42:27,950
Yes.

1434
01:42:28,304 --> 01:42:30,179
<i>Much</i> more bizarre.

1435
01:42:31,123 --> 01:42:35,486
Previously, the mansion was
shrouded in flames and burnt down...

1436
01:42:36,213 --> 01:42:39,228
But Mr. Joestar survived.

1437
01:42:40,093 --> 01:42:41,877
He beat Dio,

1438
01:42:42,563 --> 01:42:45,460
But lost everything.

1439
01:42:46,094 --> 01:42:48,640
Three days later...

1440
01:43:12,276 --> 01:43:13,449
I found it!

1441
01:43:13,492 --> 01:43:15,492
The mask that man wore!

1442
01:43:15,623 --> 01:43:17,733
If I have this mask—

1443
01:43:17,771 --> 01:43:20,799
<i>JoJo...</i>

1444
01:43:21,753 --> 01:43:24,815
<i>JoJo...</i>

1445
01:43:25,950 --> 01:43:28,791
<i>JoJo...</i>

1446
01:43:30,080 --> 01:43:33,288
<i>JoJo...</i>

1447
01:43:34,133 --> 01:43:38,276
<i>JoJo, can you hear me?</i>

1448
01:43:38,350 --> 01:43:42,833
<i>My voice calling for you?</i>

1449
01:43:46,225 --> 01:43:51,003
After carrying the unconscious Mr. Joestar
to the hospital, I came back to visit him!

